WEBVTT

00:45.646 --> 00:50.151
** [ Acoustic Guitar
Playing Intro ]

01:08.936 --> 01:12.740
* TIME IT WAS
AND WHAT A TIME IT WAS *

01:12.740 --> 01:16.144
* IT WAS *

01:16.144 --> 01:19.413
* A TIME OF INNOCENCE *

01:19.413 --> 01:24.518
* A TIME OF CONFIDENCES *

01:24.518 --> 01:27.855
* LONG AGO IT MUST BE *
[ Weeping ]

01:27.855 --> 01:31.392
* I HAVE A PHOTOGRAPH *

01:31.392 --> 01:34.862
* PRESERVE YOUR MEMORIES *

01:34.862 --> 01:38.932
* THEY'RE ALL
THAT'S LEFT YOU **

01:38.932 --> 01:41.902
[ Woman Narrating ]
HAVE YOU EVER
CONFUSED A DREAM...

01:41.902 --> 01:43.837
WITH LIFE ?

01:46.307 --> 01:50.178
OR STOLEN SOMETHING
WHEN YOU HAVE THE CASH ?

01:53.981 --> 01:56.250
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN BLUE ?

01:58.386 --> 02:03.123
OR THOUGHT YOUR TRAIN MOVING
WHILE SITTING STILL ?

02:04.292 --> 02:06.827
MAYBE I WAS JUST CRAZY.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.698
MAYBE IT WAS THE '60s.

02:12.032 --> 02:14.034
OR MAYBE
I WAS JUST A GIRL...

02:14.034 --> 02:17.438
[ Footsteps ]
INTERRUPTED.

02:17.438 --> 02:19.807
PUT HER IN RESTRAINTS.
LET'S DRAW BLOOD
FOR TOX.

02:19.807 --> 02:23.844
HOLD ON, DEAR.
GIVE HER FIVE MILLIGRAMS
OF VALIUM, I.V.

02:23.844 --> 02:27.080
TURN HER HEAD
SO SHE DOESN'T ASPIRATE.
[ Retching ]

02:27.080 --> 02:29.082
THERE YOU GO.

02:29.082 --> 02:31.385
[ Doctor 2 ]
ASPIRIN FRAGMENTS
AND VODKA, I THINK.

02:31.385 --> 02:34.622
[ Doctor 1 ]
DON'T TELL ME WHAT YOU THINK.
TAKE HER TO THE LAB.

02:34.622 --> 02:38.859
YOU SHOULD CHECK MY HAND.
THERE'S-- THERE'S NO
BONES IN IT.

02:38.859 --> 02:41.061
[ Doctor 1 ]
LOOKS LIKE A WRIST BANGER.

02:41.061 --> 02:43.063
IS THAT
WHY YOU DID THIS ?

02:43.063 --> 02:45.433
AND OTHER THINGS.

02:45.433 --> 02:48.035
[ Nurse ]
HER PARENTS ARE ON THE WAY.

02:48.035 --> 02:51.205
SOMETIMES IT'S HARD...

02:51.205 --> 02:53.807
FOR ME TO STAY IN ONE...

02:53.807 --> 02:55.609
PLACE.

02:55.609 --> 02:59.913
[ Man ]
SUSANNA, IF YOU HAD
NO BONES IN YOUR HAND,

03:02.149 --> 03:04.585
HOW DID YOU PICK UP
THE ASPIRIN ?

03:14.595 --> 03:17.398
WHAT IS MY MOTHER DOING ?

03:17.398 --> 03:20.401
WOULD YOU ANSWER
MY QUESTION, PLEASE ?

03:20.401 --> 03:22.803
HOW DID YOU PICK UP
THE ASPIRIN...

03:22.803 --> 03:25.406
IF YOU HAD NO BONES
IN YOUR HAND ?

03:26.674 --> 03:28.776
BY THEN
THEY HAD COME BACK.

03:31.879 --> 03:33.481
I SEE.

03:35.015 --> 03:37.117
NO, YOU DON'T.

03:37.117 --> 03:39.119
WELL,

03:39.119 --> 03:42.222
INDULGE ME THEN.

03:43.424 --> 03:45.559
EXPLAIN IT TO ME.

03:47.895 --> 03:49.697
EXPLAIN WHAT ?

03:49.697 --> 03:52.433
EXPLAIN TO A DOCTOR
THAT THE LAWS OF PHYSICS...

03:52.433 --> 03:54.835
CAN BE SUSPENDED ?

03:54.835 --> 03:57.838
THAT WHAT GOES UP
MAY NOT COME DOWN ?

04:03.076 --> 04:05.078
EXPLAIN...

04:05.078 --> 04:07.615
THAT TIME...

04:07.615 --> 04:11.084
CAN MOVE BACKWARDS
AND FORWARDS,

04:11.084 --> 04:13.220
AND NOW TO THEN
AND BACK AGAIN,

04:13.220 --> 04:16.957
AND YOU CAN'T CONTROL IT ?
[ Dog Barks ]

04:16.957 --> 04:19.327
WHY CAN'T YOU CONTROL IT ?

04:19.327 --> 04:21.795
[ Dog Barking ]

04:21.795 --> 04:23.597
WHAT ?

04:23.597 --> 04:26.066
WHY CAN'T YOU CONTROL TIME ?

04:26.066 --> 04:28.369
[ Barking Continues ]

04:30.170 --> 04:33.507
[ Barking Continues,
People Chattering, Laughing ]

04:38.379 --> 04:42.383
[ Chatter Grows Louder ]

04:42.383 --> 04:44.518
SAM, SHH !

04:45.519 --> 04:48.856
WHERE WERE YOU ?
EVERYONE IS HERE.

04:48.856 --> 04:50.791
COME ON.

04:53.527 --> 04:56.864
MARY, YOU REMEMBER
SUSANNA.
YES, I DO.

04:56.864 --> 04:59.633
HI.
HI.
HI.

04:59.633 --> 05:01.935
SO THIS IS WHAT
YOU'RE WEARING ?

05:01.935 --> 05:04.705
I DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS SO EARLY.
I WOULD'VE CHANGED.

05:04.705 --> 05:08.041
[ Laughs ]
HEY, EVERYBODY,
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

05:08.041 --> 05:10.077
HI !
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DAD.

05:12.413 --> 05:14.448
OH. I'M SORRY.
I WANT TO SAY
HI TO HER.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.850
SWEETIE, WOULD YOU
HOLD THIS FOR ME ?

05:16.850 --> 05:19.687
I JUST WANT TO SAY HI
TO SUSANNA.

05:19.687 --> 05:21.855
EXCUSE ME.
SUSANNA !

05:21.855 --> 05:25.025
SUSANNA !
[ Whispering ]
PROFESSOR GILCREST'S WIFE.

05:25.025 --> 05:27.561
HI. BARBARA GILCREST.
DO YOU REMEMBER ME ?

05:27.561 --> 05:30.330
BONNIE'S MOM.
I'M BONNIE'S MOM.
YEAH.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.400
YOUR SKIN
IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

05:32.400 --> 05:34.735
NOW, BONNIE WAS
IN YOUR LIT CLASS,
WASN'T SHE ?

05:34.735 --> 05:37.571
YEAH.
H-HOW IS SHE DOING ?

05:37.571 --> 05:40.173
SHE JUST GOT ACCEPTED
TO RADCLIFFE.
OH !

05:40.173 --> 05:42.175
OH, WHAT A CONUNDRUM.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.978
I'M A WELLESLEY GIRL,
MYSELF.

05:44.978 --> 05:47.781
BUT I THINK YOUNG WOMEN
SHOULD MAKE UP THEIR OWN
MIND, DON'T YOU THINK SO ?

05:47.781 --> 05:49.717
SUSANNA ?

05:52.085 --> 05:54.021
ARE YOU STONED ?

05:57.224 --> 05:59.359
DO YOU SMOKE POT ?

06:01.228 --> 06:03.664
TAKE L.S.D. ?

06:06.900 --> 06:08.836
NO DRUGS ?

06:14.107 --> 06:16.376
HOW DO YOU FEEL
RIGHT NOW ?

06:19.847 --> 06:21.782
I...

06:22.850 --> 06:24.918
DON'T KNOW.

06:24.918 --> 06:27.120
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M FEELING.

06:30.524 --> 06:32.426
YOU NEED A REST.

06:33.861 --> 06:36.797
WELL, I'LL GO HOME
AND TAKE A NAP.
NO, NO.

06:36.797 --> 06:39.733
YOU NEED TO GO SOMEWHERE
WHERE YOU CAN GET
A GENUINE REST.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.536
AND YOU'RE VERY LUCKY.

06:42.536 --> 06:45.205
THE BEST PLACE IN THE WORLD
FOR SOMEONE LIKE YOU...

06:45.205 --> 06:48.075
IS LESS THAN
A HALF AN HOUR
FROM HERE.

06:48.075 --> 06:52.145
YOU DON'T MEAN CLAYMOORE ?
SUSANNA,

06:52.145 --> 06:54.815
FOUR DAYS AGO,

06:54.815 --> 06:58.552
YOU CHASED
A BOTTLE OF ASPIRIN
WITH A BOTTLE OF VODKA.

07:00.287 --> 07:02.623
I HAD A HEADACHE.

07:05.058 --> 07:06.994
SUSANNA,

07:07.928 --> 07:10.330
YOUR FATHER
IS A FRIEND OF MINE.

07:10.330 --> 07:12.132
HE'S A COLLEAGUE.

07:12.132 --> 07:17.337
HE ASKED ME TO SEE YOU
EVEN THOUGH I DON'T
DO THIS ANYMORE.

07:17.337 --> 07:21.709
YOU'RE HURTING
EVERYONE AROUND YOU.

07:22.876 --> 07:28.215
NOW, CLAYMOORE
IS A TOP-NOTCH PLACE.

07:28.215 --> 07:30.350
A LOT OF PEOPLE GO THERE.

07:30.350 --> 07:32.486
EVEN WRITERS--

07:32.486 --> 07:34.488
LIKE YOU.

07:37.491 --> 07:39.627
[ Whispering ]
GREAT.

07:52.439 --> 07:55.909
UH, YES, I'D LIKE A CAB
AT 1240 MILFORD,
PLEASE.

07:57.511 --> 07:59.312
MY MOTHER'S HERE.

07:59.312 --> 08:03.551
IT'LL BE LESS...
EMOTIONAL
IF WE DO IT THIS WAY.

08:03.551 --> 08:06.086
YOUR PARENTS AND I
HAVE TALKED ABOUT IT.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.155
[ Radio D.J. Chattering
Indistinctly ]

08:43.756 --> 08:46.560
[ Therapist ]
NOW, MAKE SURE--
NO STOPS.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.263
BYE-BYE.

08:57.170 --> 08:59.973
[ Announcer On Radio ]
MOSTLY CLEAR TONIGHT,
WITH A LOW NEAR 60.

08:59.973 --> 09:03.543
THE OUTLOOK FOR TOMORROW
IS PARTLY CLOUDY AND MILD,
WITH A HIGH IN THE MID-70s.

09:03.543 --> 09:05.512
IT'S 69 IN BOSTON !

09:05.512 --> 09:08.115
[ On Radio ]
* WHEN YOU'RE ALONE AND
LIFE IS MAKIN' YOU LONELY *

09:08.115 --> 09:12.519
* YOU CAN ALWAYS GO
DOWNTOWN *

09:12.519 --> 09:16.724
* WHEN YOU'VE GOT WORRIES
ALL THE NOISE
AND THE HURRIES *

09:16.724 --> 09:19.326
* SEEMS TO HELP
I KNOW *

09:19.326 --> 09:21.128
* DOWNTOWN *

09:21.128 --> 09:24.932
* JUST LISTEN TO THE MUSIC
OF THE TRAFFIC IN THE CITY *

09:24.932 --> 09:29.402
* LINGER ON THE SIDEWALK
WHERE THE NEON SIGNS
ARE PRETTY **

09:29.402 --> 09:32.272
[ People ]
* ...A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *
[ Man Whispering ] SUSANNA ?

09:32.272 --> 09:35.142
* WHICH NOBODY CAN DENY *
SUSANNA ?

09:35.142 --> 09:40.013
* NOBODY CAN DENY
NOBODY CAN DENY *
SUSANNA ?

09:40.013 --> 09:42.883
[ Knock At Door ]
* FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *

09:42.883 --> 09:45.619
* HE'S A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *
SUSANNA, ARE YOU THERE ?

09:45.619 --> 09:49.022
* FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *

09:49.022 --> 09:52.259
HEY.
I WANT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.
* WHICH NOBODY CAN DENY **

09:52.259 --> 09:55.528
[ People Cheering ]
LOOK, IT WAS
A ONE-TIME THING, OKAY ?

09:55.528 --> 09:57.765
JUST COME
TO MY OFFICE TONIGHT.
[ Woman ] SWEETIE ?

09:57.765 --> 09:59.767
WHERE ARE YOU ?
WE'RE OPENING THE PRESENTS.

09:59.767 --> 10:01.702
TELL THEM YOU'RE GOING
TO A FRIEND'S.
PLEASE.

10:01.702 --> 10:05.739
WHO SHOULD I TELL FIRST--
MY PARENTS, THE DEPARTMENT
CHAIRMAN, OR YOUR WIFE ?

10:05.739 --> 10:07.875
SUSANNA. SUSANNA.
NO.

10:14.381 --> 10:16.383
[ Man ]
WHAT DID YOU DO ?

10:17.450 --> 10:19.386
WHAT DID YOU DO ?

10:21.254 --> 10:23.256
EXCUSE ME ?

10:24.925 --> 10:27.060
WELL, YOU LOOK NORMAL.

10:29.529 --> 10:32.532
I'M SAD.
[ Chuckles ]

10:32.532 --> 10:36.269
WELL,
EVERYONE'S SAD.

10:36.269 --> 10:38.071
I SEE THINGS.

10:38.071 --> 10:40.674
YOU MEAN LIKE, UH,
TRIPPIN' ?

10:42.409 --> 10:44.211
KIND OF.

10:44.211 --> 10:48.015
WELL, THEN THEY SHOULD
PUT JOHN LENNON AWAY, HUH ?

10:49.950 --> 10:52.820
I'M NOT JOHN LENNON.

10:52.820 --> 10:54.955
[ Chuckles ]

11:38.631 --> 11:41.268
DON'T GET TOO COMFORTABLE.

11:50.778 --> 11:52.880
SHOULDN'T MY PARENTS--

11:52.880 --> 11:54.882
YOU HAVE TO SIGN THEM,
MISS KAYSEN.

11:54.882 --> 11:57.417
YOU'RE OVER 18.
THIS IS YOUR DECISION.

12:05.658 --> 12:07.795
UM--

12:09.262 --> 12:11.498
I-I DIDN'T TRY
TO KILL MYSELF.

12:13.533 --> 12:18.071
THAT'S THE KIND OF THING
YOU TALK ABOUT IN THERAPY,
HONEY. NOT HERE.

12:22.709 --> 12:24.845
MISS KAYSEN ?

12:24.845 --> 12:28.882
YOU HAVE THE DISTINCTION
OF BEING THE ONLY
SENIOR AT SPRINGBROOK...

12:28.882 --> 12:30.984
NOT GOING ON TO COLLEGE.

12:36.023 --> 12:38.291
MAY I ASK
WHAT YOU PLAN TO DO ?

12:39.492 --> 12:42.029
I PLAN TO WRITE.

12:43.630 --> 12:45.833
BUT WHAT DO YOU PLAN
TO DO ?

12:47.034 --> 12:50.170
LOOK. I'M NOT GONNA
BURN MY BRA OR DROP ACID...

12:50.170 --> 12:52.172
OR GO MARCH ON WASHINGTON.

12:52.172 --> 12:55.142
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO END UP LIKE MY MOTHER.

12:55.142 --> 12:57.945
WOMEN TODAY HAVE
MORE CHOICES THAN THAT.

12:57.945 --> 13:00.713
[ Scoffs ]
NO, THEY DON'T.

13:00.713 --> 13:02.950
AND HERE.

13:04.351 --> 13:08.455
YOU FORGOT ONE, DEAR.
HERE.
OH.

13:10.223 --> 13:13.226
SPEAKING FOR DR. WICK
AND MYSELF,

13:13.226 --> 13:15.495
WELCOME TO CLAYMOORE,
SUSANNA.

13:18.966 --> 13:22.102
THIS IS THE WOMEN'S WARD,
ALSO KNOWN AS SOUTH BELL.

13:22.102 --> 13:24.104
THIS IS WHERE
YOU'LL BE STAYING,

13:24.104 --> 13:26.706
AND THIS IS
WHERE I WORK.

13:26.706 --> 13:29.642
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS THE SECOND FLOOR.

13:29.642 --> 13:33.981
I NEED YOU TO STAY CLOSE
TO ME BECAUSE IT'S EASY
TO GET LOST HERE.

13:39.119 --> 13:41.388
THIS IS OUR WARD.

13:41.388 --> 13:43.523
[ Door Closed,
Locked ]

13:43.523 --> 13:47.394
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S START WITH THIS ROOM.

13:49.396 --> 13:52.832
THIS IS THE ART ROOM.
** [ Off-Key Guitar Plucked ]

13:52.832 --> 13:54.634
POLLY.

13:54.634 --> 13:59.806
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN HERE ?
- I FEEL VERY MUSICAL TODAY.
CAN I--

13:59.806 --> 14:03.944
CAN I JUST FOR--
JUST FOR A SECOND ?
NOT TODAY, HONEY. MM-MMM.

14:11.952 --> 14:13.954
THAT'S POLLY.

14:13.954 --> 14:16.089
COME ON.

14:17.557 --> 14:19.492
[ Sighs ]

14:20.560 --> 14:22.362
MARGIE,

14:22.362 --> 14:26.199
POLLY WAS IN THE ART ROOM
BY HERSELF.
I'M SORRY, VAL.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.236
ALL RIGHT.

14:29.970 --> 14:32.105
AH, THE LIVING ROOM.

14:32.105 --> 14:34.241
EVERYONE HATES IT.

14:44.817 --> 14:46.886
AND THESE
ARE THE PHONES.

14:46.886 --> 14:50.590
YOU NEED TO MAKE A CALL,
PICK UP THE HANDLE,
TELL THE NURSE.

14:50.590 --> 14:52.392
SHE'LL CONNECT YOU.

14:52.392 --> 14:56.196
THIS IS THE NURSES' STATION,
WHICH IS SELF-EXPLANATORY,
AND THIS...

14:56.196 --> 14:59.732
IS THE TV ROOM,
WHERE EVERYONE HANGS OUT.

14:59.732 --> 15:01.734
I WANT
MY FUCKING CLOTHES !

15:01.734 --> 15:05.472
THEN YOU'LL HAVE
TO EAT SOMETHING,
WON'T YOU ?

15:06.739 --> 15:09.142
THIS IS THE CHECK-IN BOARD.
* OH, LORDY *

15:09.142 --> 15:11.078
YOU CHECK IN HERE IF YOU WANT
TO TAKE A WALK ON THE GROUNDS.
* PICK A BALE OF COTTON *

15:11.078 --> 15:13.480
* OH, LORDY
PICK A BALE OF HAY *

15:13.480 --> 15:16.316
* GOTTA JUMP DOWN, SPIN AROUND
PICK A BALE OF COTTON *

15:16.316 --> 15:19.086
* JUMP DOWN, SPIN AROUND
PICK A BALE OF HAY *

15:19.086 --> 15:22.622
* JUMP DOWN, SPIN AROUND
PICK A BALE OF COTTON **
SHE THINKS THAT BOTHERS ME.

15:22.622 --> 15:25.025
RIGHT NOW YOU'RE AN "R,"
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE
RESTRICTED TO THE WARD.

15:25.025 --> 15:28.028
BUT I THINK IN ABOUT A MONTH
YOU'LL PROBABLY MOVE UP
TO TWO-TO-ONES,

15:28.028 --> 15:30.430
WHICH IS TWO NURSES
TO EVERY PATIENT.
** [ Continues ]

15:30.430 --> 15:33.766
I'M NOT GONNA
BE HERE THAT LONG.
I'M JUST HERE FOR A REST.

15:33.766 --> 15:36.669
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
EVERYBODY GETS THE SAME TOUR
FREE OF CHARGE.

15:40.107 --> 15:42.242
[ Door Opens ]

15:43.510 --> 15:47.247
GEORGINA,
THIS IS SUSANNA,
YOUR NEW ROOMMATE.

15:47.247 --> 15:49.482
OH, GREAT. HI.
HI.

15:49.482 --> 15:52.552
YOU'RE VERY LUCKY.
GEORGINA'S AN
EXCELLENT ROOMMATE.

15:52.552 --> 15:54.354
WHY, THANK YOU, VALERIE.

15:54.354 --> 15:56.156
YOU'RE WELCOME.
VALERIE ?

15:56.156 --> 15:59.892
[ Whispering ]
THE COPS ARE BRINGING UP LISA.
THEY FOUND HER IN THE PARK.

15:59.892 --> 16:01.961
ALL RIGHT.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.963
SUSANNA,
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME ?

16:03.963 --> 16:06.399
I HAVE SOME BUSINESS
I HAVE TO ATTEND TO.

16:06.399 --> 16:08.835
GEORGINA, WILL YOU
TAKE SUSANNA DOWN
TO THE DINING ROOM...

16:08.835 --> 16:11.738
IN A HALF HOUR ?
SURE.

16:11.738 --> 16:13.840
YES MEANS YES, GEORGINA.

16:13.840 --> 16:15.975
I KNOW.

16:31.458 --> 16:33.660
GROOVY BOX.

16:34.894 --> 16:37.030
THAT.
OH !

16:37.030 --> 16:39.166
YEAH, UM,
THEY'RE FRENCH.

16:39.166 --> 16:41.534
THE FRENCH RESISTANCE
SMOKED THEM, I THINK.

16:49.276 --> 16:51.478
DID YOU EVER READ THIS ?

16:51.478 --> 16:53.280
UM, NO.

16:53.280 --> 16:56.116
I SAW THE MOVIE
A BUNCH OF TIMES, THOUGH.
OH, WELL, UM,

16:56.116 --> 16:59.952
THE MOVIE'S ACTUALLY BASED
ON THE FIRST BOOK.
I READ THAT ONE TOO,

16:59.952 --> 17:02.789
BUT THERE WERE
NO RUBY SLIPPERS
IN IT ORIGINALLY.

17:02.789 --> 17:05.558
THEY ADDED THAT.
THIS ONE TAKES PLACE
AFTERWARDS.

17:05.558 --> 17:08.861
DOROTHY DOESN'T REALLY
HAVE SUCH A BIG PART
IN THIS ONE.

17:08.861 --> 17:11.330
OH.

17:11.330 --> 17:13.733
[ Police Radio Chatter ]

17:13.733 --> 17:15.801
FUCKIN' PIG.

17:18.137 --> 17:20.272
GET OFF ME !

17:31.050 --> 17:33.052
THANKS, GRETTA.

17:33.052 --> 17:36.656
HEY, DAIS, LET ANYONE
IN YOUR ROOM YET ?

17:36.656 --> 17:38.591
HUH ?

17:40.127 --> 17:43.163
HEY, GIRLS !
HEY, SEXY.

17:43.163 --> 17:46.666
[ Kissing Noises,
Growls ]

17:46.666 --> 17:48.601
IT'S GOOD TO BE HOME !

17:51.738 --> 17:54.307
HEY, TORCH.
HEY, LISA.

17:54.307 --> 17:56.643
YOU MISS ME ?
NOT MUCH.

17:58.311 --> 18:01.281
GET HER TO HER ROOM.
GRETTA'LL DO THE STRIP SEARCH.

18:01.281 --> 18:03.650
WHO'S THAT
WITH GEORGIE-GIRL ?
COME ON.

18:03.650 --> 18:06.219
WHO IS THAT ?
WHERE'S JAMIE ?
I CAN'T DEAL WITH THIS.

18:06.219 --> 18:08.388
LISA, DON'T GIVE ME
A HARD TIME.
WHERE'S JAMIE ?

18:08.388 --> 18:10.790
WHERE IS SHE ?
WHERE'S JAMIE ?

18:10.790 --> 18:12.725
[ Lisa Shouting ]

18:14.627 --> 18:16.729
WHO ARE YOU ?

18:16.729 --> 18:20.733
HER NAME IS SUSANNA.
SHE SMOKES
FRENCH CIGARETTES.

18:20.733 --> 18:22.902
WHY IS ALL YOUR SHIT
ON HER BED ?

18:22.902 --> 18:25.905
- [ Valerie ]
LISA, OPEN THE DAMN DOOR !
- WHY ? WHERE'S JAMIE ?

18:25.905 --> 18:30.177
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT !
- [ All Shouting ]

18:30.177 --> 18:33.079
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING, LISA ?

18:33.079 --> 18:35.382
BACK OFF HER.

18:35.382 --> 18:38.618
BACK OFF !
YOU'VE BEEN GONE
FOR TWO WEEKS.

18:38.618 --> 18:41.254
A LOT OF SHIT
HAS GONE DOWN.
BACK OFF !

18:41.254 --> 18:45.192
HOW'D SHE DO IT ?
HOW'D SHE DO IT ?

18:45.192 --> 18:47.727
HOW DID SHE DO IT,
VALERIE ?

18:47.727 --> 18:49.629
GET THE FUCK
OFF ME !

18:49.629 --> 18:51.764
YOU WEAK PEOPLE.
YOU'RE ALL
WEAK FUCKING PEOPLE !

18:51.764 --> 18:55.235
YOU'RE VICTIMS !
YOU PEOPLE ARE FUCKING SICK !
[ Valerie ] GRETTA ?

18:55.235 --> 18:58.238
WHAT ? NO. NO, NO.
VAL, PLEASE.
PLEASE !

18:58.238 --> 19:00.673
NO ! NO !

19:00.673 --> 19:04.377
[ Man ]
LISA ! GET HER LEGS !
[ Clamoring ]

19:04.377 --> 19:06.546
FUCK YOU ! NO !
GET HER FEET !

19:06.546 --> 19:09.182
I GOT HER.
GET OFF ME !
NO ! NO ! NO !

19:09.182 --> 19:13.186
NO ! NO ! NO !
NO ! NO !
GET OFF !

19:17.557 --> 19:20.260
WE HAVE GOT TO CUT
THOSE NAILS AGAIN.

19:20.260 --> 19:23.763
[ Sobbing, Muttering ]

19:26.466 --> 19:30.337
MY GOD.
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT ?

19:30.337 --> 19:32.339
THAT WAS LISA.

19:32.339 --> 19:36.075
AND JAMIE
WAS YOUR ROOMMATE ?

19:36.075 --> 19:37.910
JAMIE WAS LISA'S
BEST FRIEND.

19:37.910 --> 19:40.880
SHE WAS SAD LAST WEEK
'CAUSE LISA RAN AWAY,

19:40.880 --> 19:43.550
SO SHE HUNG HERSELF
WITH A VOLLEYBALL NET.

19:47.620 --> 19:51.224
MASTER ?
OOH ! OH, I'M SORRY.

19:51.224 --> 19:53.493
[ Both Giggling ]

19:53.493 --> 19:55.628
[ Woman ]
MEDS !

19:57.964 --> 19:59.899
CYNTHIA CROWLEY.

20:00.967 --> 20:03.803
SUSANNA KAYSEN.

20:04.971 --> 20:07.274
SUSANNA KAYSEN !

20:08.908 --> 20:11.644
I AM MRS. McWILLEY,
AND THESE ARE
FOR YOU.

20:11.644 --> 20:14.781
WHAT ARE THEY ?
THEY'LL HELP YOU SLEEP.

20:14.781 --> 20:17.784
- IT'S 10:30. I'M NOT GONNA--
- FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.

20:17.784 --> 20:20.653
YOU CAN DISCUSS IT
IN THE MORNING, DEAR,
WITH YOUR DOCTOR.

20:20.653 --> 20:23.490
IN THE MEANTIME,
WE'LL JUST HAVE
TO AGREE TO DISAGREE.

20:26.793 --> 20:29.396
TAKE THEM HERE.
HAVE SOME WATER.

20:31.831 --> 20:33.766
POLLY CLARK.

20:35.001 --> 20:36.936
YOU CAN GO NOW.

20:41.207 --> 20:43.343
TERESA McCULLIAN.

20:49.015 --> 20:50.950
DAISY RANDONE.

20:54.421 --> 20:56.556
ANGELA COURY.

21:00.159 --> 21:02.362
JACQUELINE LIGHTS.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.033
DONNA SMITH.

21:09.502 --> 21:11.638
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

21:37.530 --> 21:39.799
[ Voices Echoing ]

21:39.799 --> 21:43.703
[ Man ]
...ALL THE WAY
TO PRINCETON UNIVERSITY.

21:43.703 --> 21:46.138
[ Applause ]

21:46.138 --> 21:49.342
[ McWilley Continues ]

21:49.342 --> 21:52.412
[ Man Continuing ]
...YEARBOOK EDITOR,
AND MEMBER OF THE HONOR
SOCIETY,

21:52.412 --> 21:54.414
HEADING OFF
TO TULANE UNIVERSITY.

21:54.414 --> 21:56.949
[ Applause ]
CONGRATULATIONS, SON.

21:56.949 --> 22:02.455
ANDREA JACOBS,
PRESIDENT OF THE FRENCH CLUB
AND HONOR SOCIETY,

22:02.455 --> 22:05.324
AND ON HER WAY
TO SARAH LAWRENCE.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.762
SUSANNA KAYSEN.

22:11.330 --> 22:13.966
WHAT IS SHE DOING ?
SOME KIND OF A STUNT.

22:13.966 --> 22:17.370
[ Crowd Murmuring ]
SUSANNA KAYSEN.

22:21.107 --> 22:24.010
[ Feedback Whines ]
SUSANNA KAYSEN.

22:24.010 --> 22:27.447
[ Boy ]
WAKE UP, YOU FREAK.
[ Door Opens ]

22:27.447 --> 22:29.716
[ Whispering ]
CHECKS.

22:36.322 --> 22:38.458
[ Door Closes ]

22:44.230 --> 22:46.599
[ Whispering ]
GEORGINA.

22:49.235 --> 22:51.370
WHY DO THEY
DO THAT ?

22:52.639 --> 22:55.041
THEY'RE JUST DOING CHECKS.

22:55.041 --> 22:58.645
THEY'LL SPACE THEM OUT
MORE AFTER YOU'VE
BEEN HERE A WHILE.

23:03.182 --> 23:06.118
THAT GIRL, POLLY.

23:07.587 --> 23:09.856
HOW DID SHE GET ALL--

23:11.057 --> 23:13.125
WHEN SHE WAS TEN,

23:13.125 --> 23:16.596
HER MOTHER TOLD HER
THAT SHE HAD TO GIVE AWAY
HER PUPPY...

23:16.596 --> 23:19.932
'CAUSE HE WAS GIVING HER
A RASH.

23:19.932 --> 23:22.902
SO POLLY WENT...

23:22.902 --> 23:26.473
AND FOUND
HER FATHER'S GAS CAN,

23:26.473 --> 23:30.677
AND SHE POURED IT
ALL OVER WHERE SHE WAS
GETTING THE RASH.

23:31.544 --> 23:33.680
AND THEN...

23:35.147 --> 23:37.450
SHE LIT A MATCH.

23:38.918 --> 23:40.853
OH, MY GOD.

23:46.425 --> 23:48.861
WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU ?
WHY ARE YOU HERE ?

23:49.729 --> 23:52.832
PSEUDOLOGIA FANTASTICA.

23:54.166 --> 23:56.736
WHAT'S THAT ?

23:57.704 --> 24:01.774
I'M A PATHOLOGICAL LIAR.

24:06.212 --> 24:09.148
** [ Rock On Radio ]

24:11.751 --> 24:14.153
* TIME HAS COME TODAY *

24:15.622 --> 24:18.024
* YOUNG HEARTS
CAN GO THEIR WAY *

24:19.892 --> 24:22.829
* CAN'T PUT IT OFF
ANOTHER DAY *

24:24.030 --> 24:26.866
* I DON'T CARE
WHAT OTHERS SAY *

24:26.866 --> 24:30.637
* THEY THINK
WE DON'T LISTEN ANYWAY *

24:30.637 --> 24:34.641
* TIME HAS COME TODAY *

24:34.641 --> 24:36.776
* HEY *

24:38.244 --> 24:41.113
** [ Grows Louder ]

24:41.113 --> 24:42.915
* OH *

24:42.915 --> 24:46.653
* THE RULES
HAVE CHANGED TODAY *
* HEY *

24:46.653 --> 24:50.590
* I HAVE NO PLANS TO STAY *
* HEY *

24:50.590 --> 24:54.594
* I'M THINKING ABOUT
THOSE OTHER WAYS *
* HEY *

24:54.594 --> 24:57.063
** [ Continues ]
HEY, WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS
THIS FALL ?

24:57.063 --> 24:59.666
WHAT ?
WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS
THIS FALL ?

24:59.666 --> 25:01.868
I DON'T HAVE ANY.

25:01.868 --> 25:04.470
I'M GOING TO BE
AN ETHNOBOTANIST.

25:04.470 --> 25:07.740
FULL SCHOLARSHIP TO M.I.T.

25:07.740 --> 25:09.742
I'M GONNA JOIN
THE KRISHNAS.

25:09.742 --> 25:14.080
HARE KRISHNA ?
THAT'S INTERESTING, ACTUALLY.

25:14.080 --> 25:16.015
I WAS KIDDING.

25:17.717 --> 25:19.852
** [ Continues ]

25:26.025 --> 25:29.095
* NOW THE TIME HAS COME *

25:29.095 --> 25:31.330
* TIME *
* THERE'S NO PLACE TO RUN *

25:31.330 --> 25:33.633
YOU'RE SUSANNA,
RIGHT ?

25:33.633 --> 25:38.170
** [ Continues ]
I'M TOBY.
ANDREA JACOBS' BROTHER.

25:39.639 --> 25:43.142
I WAS AT GRADUATION.
[ Sighs ]

25:44.310 --> 25:45.912
YOU'RE, UH--

25:47.747 --> 25:49.515
YOU'RE PRETTY
WHEN YOU SLEEP.
* TIME **

25:49.515 --> 25:51.550
CHECKS.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.686
IT'S 7:00.

26:08.400 --> 26:12.004
I MEAN, EVERYBODY
THINKS ABOUT IT
AT SOME POINT.

26:13.873 --> 26:16.008
HOW WOULD YOU DO IT ?

26:17.810 --> 26:19.812
I DON'T KNOW.

26:19.812 --> 26:22.381
I GUESS I HAVEN'T
REALLY THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

26:22.381 --> 26:27.019
* THE SUMMER HAD INHALED
AND HELD ITS BREATH
TOO LONG **

26:28.487 --> 26:31.023
SEE, ONCE IT'S
IN YOUR HEAD, THOUGH,

26:31.023 --> 26:33.025
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]

26:33.025 --> 26:37.096
YOU BECOME THIS...
STRANGE NEW BREED--

26:37.096 --> 26:42.869
A LIFE-FORM THAT
LOVES TO FANTASIZE
ABOUT ITS OWN DEMISE.

26:42.869 --> 26:46.505
MAKE A STUPID REMARK,
KILL YOURSELF.

26:46.505 --> 26:48.507
YOU LIKE THE MOVIE,
YOU LIVE.

26:48.507 --> 26:50.509
YOU MISS THE TRAIN,
KILL YOURSELF.

26:50.509 --> 26:53.312
SUSANNA.
WHAT ?

26:53.312 --> 26:57.249
LET'S NOT TALK ABOUT THIS
ANYMORE, OKAY ?

26:57.249 --> 26:59.185
WHY ?

27:02.822 --> 27:07.226
BECAUSE...
IT'S, UH, STUPID.

27:13.565 --> 27:16.736
[ Groans ]
WHAT ?

27:20.272 --> 27:22.074
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?

27:22.074 --> 27:25.611
OH, WHAT ?
'CAUSE I DON'T
WANT TO KILL MYSELF,

27:25.611 --> 27:27.313
THAT'S NOT COOL TO YOU ?

27:28.748 --> 27:30.750
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.
I WAS JUST TALKING.

27:30.750 --> 27:33.953
LOOK, SUSANNA,
THE WORLD IS FUCKED UP,
OKAY ?

27:33.953 --> 27:36.255
ALL RIGHT,
IT'S SO FUCKED UP
THAT IF SOME--

27:36.255 --> 27:39.325
SOME DRAFT ZOMBIE
PULLS MY BIRTHDAY
OUT OF A BARREL,

27:39.325 --> 27:41.493
I'M GONNA DIE.

27:41.493 --> 27:44.063
WHEN'S YOUR BIRTHDAY ?

27:46.098 --> 27:48.034
DECEMBER 30.

27:50.536 --> 27:54.040
- I'LL PRAY FOR YOU.
- HEY. SUSANNA.

27:54.941 --> 27:58.077
- CHECKS ?
- [ Gasps ]

28:01.613 --> 28:03.750
[ Door Closes ]

28:06.886 --> 28:09.288
[ Sighs ]
[ Gretta ]
CHECKS.

28:20.299 --> 28:22.234
[ Door Opens ]

28:24.036 --> 28:26.172
[ Valerie ]
YOU ASKED FOR THIS ?

28:36.048 --> 28:40.452
- ARE YOU GONNA WATCH ?
- 'FRAID SO.

28:40.452 --> 28:43.923
THAT'S WHY THERE'S SO MANY
FUZZY-LEGGED WOMEN AROUND HERE.

28:47.927 --> 28:50.629
HAS ANYBODY EVER WATCHED YOU
SHAVE YOUR LEGS ?

28:50.629 --> 28:54.867
I GOT TWO KIDS
AND ONE BATHROOM.
WHAT DO YOU THINK ?

28:55.935 --> 28:58.337
I THINK YOU SHOULD
LOCK THE DOOR.

29:00.106 --> 29:04.243
[ Man Over P.A. ]
SEPTEMBER 14.

29:04.243 --> 29:06.245
[ Man 2 ]
SEPTEMBER 14 ?

29:06.245 --> 29:08.580
[ Man 1 Continues,
Indistinct ]

29:08.580 --> 29:09.949
[ Woman ]
BINGO.

29:11.750 --> 29:14.386
BINGO. BINGO.
[ Man #1 ]
DECEMBER 30.

29:15.454 --> 29:17.456
OH, MY GOD.

29:17.456 --> 29:19.391
[ Woman ]
BINGO.

29:21.227 --> 29:24.596
A GUY I KNOW
WAS JUST DRAFTED.

29:24.596 --> 29:26.899
WHAT'S HIS NAME ?

29:28.467 --> 29:30.269
TOBY.

29:30.269 --> 29:32.471
[ TV Continues,
Indistinct ]
BINGO.

29:32.471 --> 29:35.441
HE'S DEAD NOW.
BINGO.

29:37.209 --> 29:38.477
BINGO.

29:40.679 --> 29:43.215
[ Daisy ]
GET OUT, LISA !
I'M NOT IN YOUR ROOM, DAISY.

29:43.215 --> 29:46.118
I'M RIGHT FUCKIN' HERE.
I WAS GONNA OFFER YOU
SOME OF MY NAIL POLISH.

29:46.118 --> 29:48.120
GET OUT !
[ Door Slams ]

29:48.120 --> 29:50.890
[ Chuckling ]
YOU'RE LOOKING
BETTER, LISA.

29:50.890 --> 29:53.059
WHY, THANKS, MARGIE.

29:53.059 --> 29:55.061
HOW'S THE ENGAGEMENT
GOING ?
OH, YOU KNOW.

29:55.061 --> 29:57.029
NO, I DON'T.
I'VE BEEN AWAY.

29:57.029 --> 30:00.599
JOE WANTS ME TO...
BEFORE THE WEDDING.

30:00.599 --> 30:04.670
FUCK HIS BRAINS OUT.
USE A RUBBER.
[ Giggling ]

30:04.670 --> 30:07.806
GOSH, I DON'T KNOW.
YEAH !

30:26.825 --> 30:28.794
CAN I BUM ONE ?

30:28.794 --> 30:31.230
GO AHEAD.

30:50.282 --> 30:51.918
HUH.

30:53.252 --> 30:56.588
SO. HAVE YOU HAD
YOUR FIRST MELVIN YET ?

30:56.588 --> 30:58.390
WHO'S THAT ?

30:58.390 --> 31:02.028
BALD GUY
WITH A LITTLE PECKER
AND A FAT WIFE.

31:02.028 --> 31:04.163
YOUR "THER-RAPIST,"
SWEAT PEA.

31:05.597 --> 31:09.335
UNLESS, UH--
UNLESS THEY'RE
GIVING YOU SHOCKS.

31:09.335 --> 31:11.603
OR, GOD FORBID,
LETTING YOU OUT.

31:11.603 --> 31:14.540
THEN YOU GET TO SEE
THE GREAT, WONDERFUL
DR. DYKE.

31:14.540 --> 31:16.475
SHE MEANS
DR. WICK.

31:18.344 --> 31:21.147
I'VE BEEN IN HIS OFFICE,
BUT I HAVEN'T MET HIM YET.

31:21.147 --> 31:23.482
HE'S A SHE.
DR. WICK'S A GIRL.

31:23.482 --> 31:26.085
THAT'S RIGHT, M.G.
WICK'S A CHICK.
WICK'S A CHICK.

31:26.085 --> 31:29.221
[ Woman ]
LISA !
HENCE THE NICKNAME.

31:29.221 --> 31:33.592
OH ! HEY, LIL.
WHEN THE FUCK
IS MY CHECKUP ?

31:33.592 --> 31:36.895
NOW. IT'S NOW, LISA.
YOU SAID YOU'D BE
IN YOUR ROOM.

31:36.895 --> 31:40.099
CAN'T LET YOU SIT TOO LONG
WITHOUT POPPING THE HOOD, HUH ?

31:55.447 --> 31:57.049
ASSHOLE.

31:57.049 --> 31:59.251
[ Margie ]
SUSANNA, YOU HAVE MELVIN
IN HALF AN HOUR.

31:59.251 --> 32:02.654
I'LL TAKE YOU THERE.
I-- I'M SORRY.

32:04.523 --> 32:07.326
[ Man ]
WHY ARE YOU USING
THE PAST TENSE ?

32:07.326 --> 32:09.328
[ Susanna ]
WHAT DO YOU MEAN ?

32:09.328 --> 32:12.931
WELL, HE WAS
ONLY DRAFTED TODAY,

32:12.931 --> 32:16.335
SO CHANCES ARE
HE'S NOT DEAD YET.

32:16.335 --> 32:19.938
PROBABLY HAS SEVERAL
MONTHS...

32:19.938 --> 32:22.274
BEFORE HE EVEN REPORTS.

32:23.475 --> 32:25.944
HE WAS JUST A NICE GUY,
THAT'S ALL,

32:25.944 --> 32:28.580
AND IT MADE ME FEEL BAD.

32:28.580 --> 32:30.582
YOU'VE BEEN FEELING BAD
IN GENERAL.

32:30.582 --> 32:34.286
RIGHT ?
YOU'VE BEEN
FEELING DEPRESSED ?

32:35.754 --> 32:39.625
WELL, I HAVEN'T EXACTLY
BEEN A BALL OF JOY,
MELVIN.

32:39.625 --> 32:43.229
I UNDERSTAND YOU TRIED
TO KILL YOURSELF
LAST WEEK.

32:43.229 --> 32:46.232
ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO TELL ME ABOUT THAT ?

32:46.232 --> 32:47.566
I HAD A HEADACHE.

32:49.635 --> 32:52.571
SO I ASSUME YOU TOOK
THE RECOMMENDED
ASPIRIN DOSAGE...

32:52.571 --> 32:54.640
FOR A HEADACHE.

32:54.640 --> 32:58.377
I DIDN'T TRY TO KILL MYSELF.
WHAT WERE YOU TRYING
TO DO ?

32:58.377 --> 33:00.979
I WAS TRYING
TO MAKE THE SHIT STOP.

33:00.979 --> 33:04.150
THE TIME JUMPS,
THE DEPRESSION,

33:04.150 --> 33:07.719
THE, UH, HEADACHES,
THE THING WITH YOUR HAND ?

33:09.155 --> 33:11.290
ALL OF THE ABOVE.

33:13.359 --> 33:15.294
I SEE.

33:16.428 --> 33:20.132
[ Faintly ]
PAUL IS DEAD !

33:23.769 --> 33:25.137
SUSANNA ?

33:27.473 --> 33:30.209
WHAT IS IT ?
ARE YOU PUZZLED
ABOUT SOMETHING ?

33:31.910 --> 33:34.012
YEAH, I GUESS I AM,
MELVIN.

33:34.012 --> 33:36.014
I GUESS I'M PUZZLED
AS TO WHY IT IS...

33:36.014 --> 33:37.916
I HAVE TO BE
IN A MENTAL INSTITUTION.

33:37.916 --> 33:40.086
YOU-YOU PUT YOURSELF HERE.

33:40.086 --> 33:42.088
MY PARENTS PUT ME HERE.

33:42.088 --> 33:46.058
NO. NO, THEY DIDN'T.

33:46.058 --> 33:48.894
EVERYONE HERE'S
FUCKING CRAZY !

33:48.894 --> 33:51.130
YOU WANT TO GO HOME.

33:54.032 --> 33:56.402
SAME PROBLEM.

33:56.402 --> 33:59.671
[ High-Pitched Voice ]
M.G., LOOK AT ME.

33:59.671 --> 34:01.540
PLAY WITH ME.

34:01.540 --> 34:05.777
DON'T BE SAD.
DON'T BE SAD.

34:05.777 --> 34:07.779
HEY.
LISA.

34:07.779 --> 34:10.482
[ Lisa ]
YEAH.

34:13.819 --> 34:15.821
AAH.
THANK YOU.

34:15.821 --> 34:17.856
MM-HMM.

34:17.856 --> 34:20.492
[ Footsteps ]

34:23.395 --> 34:25.731
[ Indistinct
Conversation ]

34:30.869 --> 34:32.804
HI.

34:35.607 --> 34:37.643
[ Lisa Sighs ]

34:38.877 --> 34:40.812
[ No Audio ]

34:46.585 --> 34:47.719
SUSANNA.

34:49.920 --> 34:53.192
OH. WHAT ARE THESE ?
COLACE.
IT'S JUST A LAXATIVE.

34:53.192 --> 34:55.360
OH, I DON'T--
I DON'T NEED THEM.

34:55.360 --> 34:57.496
ARE WE GOING
TO HAVE A PROBLEM ?

34:59.498 --> 35:01.700
[ Lisa To Puppet ]
ARE WE GOING TO HAVE
A PROBLEM ?

35:01.700 --> 35:04.270
ARE WE GOING
TO HAVE
A PROBLEM ?

35:04.270 --> 35:06.272
MAY I SEE ?

35:06.272 --> 35:09.141
THANK YOU.
SURRENDER.

35:10.142 --> 35:12.278
ARE WE GOING
TO HAVE A PROBLEM ?

35:13.279 --> 35:15.914
NO ? NO PROBLEM.

35:15.914 --> 35:18.550
SUSANNA ?
PHONE CALL, BOOTH ONE.

35:21.887 --> 35:24.690
HELLO ?
[ Woman ]
HOLD ON.

35:24.690 --> 35:27.559
HELLO ?
[ Woman Shouting ]
SUSANNA ?

35:27.559 --> 35:29.928
HI, MOM.
HI, HONEY.
YOUR FATHER'S ON TOO.

35:29.928 --> 35:33.098
HE JUST GOT BACK
FROM RESERVE HEARINGS.
HIS PLANE GOT STUCK AT DULLES.

35:33.098 --> 35:35.301
[ Father ]
HOW YOU DOING, HONEY ?
[ Shouting ]

35:35.301 --> 35:38.003
I'M FINE, DAD.
[ Mother ]
YOU KNOW, SWEETHEART--

35:38.003 --> 35:39.805
[ Continues, Indistinct ]
OH, GOD !

35:39.805 --> 35:41.807
THAT'S WHAT DOCTOR--
VALERIE ?
VALERIE, PLEASE.

35:41.807 --> 35:44.576
IF YOU CAN'T GIVE ME
ANY EX-LAX, CAN I PLEASE
HAVE SOME COLACE ?

35:44.576 --> 35:46.712
[ Valerie ]
NO. NO MORE LAXATIVES.

35:46.712 --> 35:49.448
MARGIE ?
I CAN GET HER
SOME PRUNE JUICE.

35:49.448 --> 35:52.751
[ Laughs ]
PRUNE JUICE !

35:52.751 --> 35:55.120
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS.
[ Mother Continues,
Indistinct ]

35:55.120 --> 35:57.456
...SHE WAS WONDERING
WHETHER YOU'D MADE
ANY NEW FRIENDS,

35:57.456 --> 35:59.558
AND I SAID, "NO, MOM.

35:59.558 --> 36:02.628
THIS ISN'T CAMP WINNETKA."

36:02.628 --> 36:06.131
** [ Radio Playing ]

36:06.131 --> 36:09.535
DAISY ?
[ Daisy ]
FUCK OFF.

36:09.535 --> 36:11.670
I HAVE SOMETHING YOU WANT.

36:14.273 --> 36:16.675
[ Footsteps ]

36:18.610 --> 36:20.346
COME IN.

36:20.346 --> 36:24.716
[ Door Opens ]
* QUE SERA, SERA
WHATEVER WILL BE *

36:24.716 --> 36:26.818
* WILL BE *

36:26.818 --> 36:30.088
* THE FUTURE'S NOT OURS
TO SEE *

36:30.088 --> 36:34.460
* QUE SERA, SERA *

36:34.460 --> 36:38.797
* WHAT WILL BE
WILL BE **

36:38.797 --> 36:40.732
** [ Continues ]

36:50.409 --> 36:52.411
YOU'RE ALL PACKED UP.

36:52.411 --> 36:55.347
YEAH. I'M LEAVING
IN A MONTH.

36:55.347 --> 36:57.148
MY DAD GOT ME
AN APARTMENT.

36:57.148 --> 37:01.219
REALLY ? WHERE ?
WHAT KIND OF--
IT'S NEAR THE AIRPORT.

37:01.219 --> 37:03.955
ONE BEDROOM, TWO BATHS,
EAT-IN CHICKEN.

37:03.955 --> 37:07.293
HE FIXED IT UP
REAL NICE FOR ME.
YOU MEAN "EAT-IN KITCHEN."

37:07.293 --> 37:10.429
THAT'S WHAT I SAID, ASSHOLE.

37:10.429 --> 37:12.831
SO WHAT DO YOU HAVE
THAT I WANT ?

37:16.435 --> 37:18.937
PUT IT ON THE BED
AND GET OUT.

37:18.937 --> 37:22.608
- PUT YOURS ON THE BED.
- OH, JESUS. GET OUT !

37:22.608 --> 37:26.978
- GET OUT !
- DAIS, DON'T TAKE ADVANTAGE
JUST 'CAUSE SHE'S NEW.

37:26.978 --> 37:30.516
PONY UP SOME VALIUM.
GET THE FUCK OUT,
OR I'M CALLING VALERIE !

37:30.516 --> 37:33.585
- VALERIE !
- WHY DON'T YOU
CALL VALERIE ?

37:33.585 --> 37:35.587
LET'S CALL VALERIE
AND ASK HER FOR SOME COLACE,

37:35.587 --> 37:37.656
JUST LIKE SUSIE Q's GOT
IN HER FUCKIN' HAND.

37:37.656 --> 37:39.658
WHY DOES IT STINK IN HERE ?

37:39.658 --> 37:43.929
- I DON'T TAKE VALIUM.
- [ Lisa ] I KNOW, DAISY.
THAT'S THE POINT.

37:43.929 --> 37:46.798
YOU DON'T TAKE THEM.
THEY GIVE THEM TO YOU,
AND YOU DON'T TAKE THEM.

37:46.798 --> 37:48.800
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
ARE YOU GONNA EAT THAT,
OR-OR--

37:48.800 --> 37:52.404
CHECKS.
HEY, YOU'VE GOT
VISITORS, DAISY.

37:52.404 --> 37:54.506
I WANT SOME FUCKING COLACE.

37:54.506 --> 37:56.642
TALK TO MELVIN TOMORROW.

38:07.853 --> 38:11.923
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK ?
I THINK YOU WANT
TO POOP, DAISY.

38:11.923 --> 38:14.360
I THINK IT'S BEEN DAYS.

38:15.594 --> 38:18.063
LOOK IT'S OKAY.
I DON'T CARE.
I DO !

38:18.063 --> 38:19.998
I DO CARE.

38:22.734 --> 38:26.438
SO, DADDY BUYS YOU A PRIVATE
AND NO ONE GETS IN, HUH ?

38:28.239 --> 38:31.076
YOU NEVER LEAVE,
EXCEPT FOR WHEN VALERIE
MAKES YOU GO TO THE CAFETERIA,

38:31.076 --> 38:33.445
WHERE, UH, YOU NEVER EAT.

38:33.445 --> 38:35.447
YOU'RE A LAXATIVE JUNKIE,
SO...

38:35.447 --> 38:37.282
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU WERE LIKE JANET.

38:37.282 --> 38:41.353
BUT THEN--
BUT THEN HERE YOU ARE
WITH THIS FUCKING CHICKEN.

38:41.353 --> 38:44.856
[ Imitates Chicken ]
SO WHAT'S WITH THAT, HUH ?

38:44.856 --> 38:48.894
MY DAD OWNS A DELI, ASSHOLE,
WITH A ROTISSERIE.

38:48.894 --> 38:52.063
I LIKE MY DAD'S CHICKEN,
AND WHEN I EAT SOMETHING ELSE,
I PUKE.

38:52.063 --> 38:54.933
OH.
BUT WHY DO YOU
EAT IT HERE ?

38:54.933 --> 38:58.069
WHY DON'T YOU LIKE
TO GO TO THE CAFETERIA ?

38:58.069 --> 39:00.038
WHICH DO YOU LIKE BETTER ?

39:00.038 --> 39:02.874
TAKING A DUMP ALONE,
OR WITH VALERIE WATCHING ?

39:02.874 --> 39:04.743
ALONE.

39:04.743 --> 39:08.414
[ Daisy ]
EVERYONE LIKES TO BE ALONE
WHEN IT COMES OUT.

39:08.414 --> 39:10.482
I LIKE TO BE ALONE
WHEN IT GOES IN.

39:10.482 --> 39:13.685
TO ME, THE CAFETERIA
IS LIKE BEING...

39:13.685 --> 39:16.154
WITH 20 GIRLS ALL AT ONCE,
TAKING A DUMP.

39:16.154 --> 39:19.391
THAT IS FUCKED UP, DAISY.

39:20.959 --> 39:24.596
COME ON.
COME ON.

39:26.331 --> 39:28.333
ALL RIGHT. ASSHOLES.

39:28.333 --> 39:30.469
FINE. HERE.

39:35.407 --> 39:37.876
HERE.

39:46.317 --> 39:49.054
NO ! LISA, DON'T !

39:49.054 --> 39:51.289
NO, NO, NO, NO !
PLEASE.

39:51.289 --> 39:53.625
DIOS FUCKING MIO.

39:53.625 --> 39:56.261
[ Coughs ]
UGH.

39:56.261 --> 39:59.230
[ Lisa ]
I GUESS THAT'S HOW DADDY
KNOWS SHE'S EATING.

39:59.230 --> 40:01.232
WHEN I GET FIVE,
[ Lisa Laughing ]

40:01.232 --> 40:03.635
VALERIE MAKES ME
THROW THEM AWAY.

40:16.848 --> 40:18.850
SCRIBBLE, SCRIBBLE,
SCRIBBLE.
[ Gasps ]

40:18.850 --> 40:22.754
- WRITTEN ANYTHING
ABOUT ME YET ?
- DON'T DO THAT !

40:24.022 --> 40:25.957
OKAY.

40:32.664 --> 40:36.535
LISA, IS DAISY
REALLY GETTING OUT ?

40:38.804 --> 40:42.808
YEAH. SHE COUGHED UP
A BIG ONE.

40:42.808 --> 40:47.078
B-BUT HOW CAN--
I MEAN, SHE'S... INSANE.

40:47.078 --> 40:50.081
YEAH, WELL, THAT'S WHAT
"THER-RAPE-ME" IS ALL ABOUT.

40:50.081 --> 40:53.819
THAT'S WHY FUCKIN' FREUD'S
PICTURE'S ON EVERY
SHRINK'S WALL.

40:53.819 --> 40:55.687
HE CREATED A FUCKIN' INDUSTRY.

40:55.687 --> 41:00.158
YOU LIE DOWN,
CONFESS YOUR SECRETS,
AND YOU'RE SAVED. "KA-CHING !"

41:00.158 --> 41:04.462
AND, THE MORE YOU CONFESS,
THE MORE THEY THINK
ABOUT SETTING YOU FREE.

41:04.462 --> 41:07.065
BUT WHAT IF YOU DON'T
HAVE A SECRET ?

41:08.867 --> 41:11.002
THEN YOU'RE A LIFER,
LIKE ME.

41:12.170 --> 41:14.740
I WAS CHANGING HER DIAPER,

41:14.740 --> 41:16.742
AND I TURNED
TO GET THE POWDER,

41:16.742 --> 41:20.879
AND WHILE
MY BACK WAS TURNED,
SHE ROLLED OFF THE BED.

41:23.148 --> 41:26.017
SHE ROLLED OFF THE BED
AND BROKE HER LEG.

41:27.452 --> 41:29.087
AND THE DOCTOR PUT HER
IN A BODY CAST,

41:29.087 --> 41:31.557
BUT HE ALSO
STRAPPED HER DOWN.

41:31.557 --> 41:33.992
- [ Father ] ANNETTE,
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO--
- YOU NEVER TOLD ME THIS.

41:33.992 --> 41:36.461
[ Annette ]
CARL HAD BEEN PLANNING
THIS TRIP TO SANTA MONICA.

41:36.461 --> 41:38.730
HE HAD A COMMITMENT
AT RAND.

41:38.730 --> 41:40.899
SO WE--
WE TOOK HER WITH US,

41:40.899 --> 41:44.736
ON THE BACK SEAT,
STRAPPED TO THIS BOARD,
4,000 MILES.

41:44.736 --> 41:47.005
IF YOU LIKE, MRS. KAYSEN,
WE CAN...

41:47.005 --> 41:51.242
DISCUSS THIS, UH, FURTHER
ON THE WAY OUT, BUT, UH--

41:51.242 --> 41:54.479
JUST HOW LONG
IS MY DAUGHTER
GOING TO BE HERE ?

41:54.479 --> 41:56.281
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
MR. KAYSEN,

41:56.281 --> 42:00.752
PSYCHIATRY AND ECONOMICS
ARE, UH-- ARE DIFFERENT.

42:00.752 --> 42:03.822
THE LENGTH OF SUSANNA'S STAY
ISN'T FIXED.

42:03.822 --> 42:07.659
UH, IT DEPENDS
ON HER RESPONSE TO TREATMENT.

42:07.659 --> 42:09.661
[ Carl ]
FOR WHAT ? DEPRESSION ?

42:09.661 --> 42:11.496
LOOK,
IT'S ALMOST CHRISTMAS.

42:11.496 --> 42:15.601
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO SAY
TO THE PEOPLE BACK HOME
WHO CARE ABOUT HER ?

42:15.601 --> 42:18.236
YOU SEE, MELVIN,
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE...

42:18.236 --> 42:22.641
IS MY PARENTS ARE HAVING
A LITTLE HOLIDAY COCKTAIL
CHRISTMAS PARTY CRISIS.

42:22.641 --> 42:24.776
[ Carl ]
SUSANNA !
WHAT ?

42:26.311 --> 42:29.480
SO WHAT IS THIS "BORDERLINE"
BUSINESS YOU MENTIONED
ON THE PHONE ?

42:29.480 --> 42:31.917
UH, UM--

42:31.917 --> 42:35.020
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S USEFUL...
TO SUSANNA.

42:35.020 --> 42:37.589
I MEAN, NOT, UH--
WHAT "BORDERLINE BUSINESS" ?

42:37.589 --> 42:39.490
SEE, THE MIND...
BORDERLINE WHAT ?

42:39.490 --> 42:42.060
IS THE--
BORDERLINE BETWEEN
WHAT AND WHAT ?

42:42.060 --> 42:45.130
MELVIN.
IT'S A CONDITION, SUSANNA,

42:45.130 --> 42:47.933
AND IT'S CALLED BORDERLINE
PERSONALITY DISORDER.

42:47.933 --> 42:49.868
OH, GOD.

42:50.769 --> 42:52.771
IT'S NOT UNCOMMON,

42:52.771 --> 42:55.473
ESPECIALLY AMONG
YOUNG WOMEN.

42:55.473 --> 42:57.275
WELL, WHAT CAUSES IT ?

42:57.275 --> 43:00.011
WE'RE--
WE'RE REALLY NOT SURE.

43:00.011 --> 43:03.081
IS IT GENETIC ?
OH, CHRIST !

43:03.081 --> 43:06.952
IT IS FIVE TIMES
MORE COMMON...

43:06.952 --> 43:09.988
AMONG THOSE
WITH A BORDERLINE...

43:09.988 --> 43:11.923
PARENT.

43:13.825 --> 43:16.094
I-I CAN'T DO THIS.

43:16.094 --> 43:18.830
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T.
I CAN'T DO THIS.

43:18.830 --> 43:23.702
** [ Marching Band ]

43:32.978 --> 43:35.714
"RAZORS PAIN YOU,
RIVERS ARE DAMP.

43:35.714 --> 43:37.716
"ACID STAINS YOU,
DRUGS CAUSE CRAMP.

43:37.716 --> 43:39.718
"GUNS AREN'T LAWFUL,
NOOSES GIVE.

43:39.718 --> 43:43.021
GAS SMELLS AWFUL,
YOU MIGHT AS WELL LIVE."

43:43.021 --> 43:44.656
GIN.

43:44.656 --> 43:49.895
[ Man On TV ]
...ONE OF OUR OLD FAVORITES,
MURPHY THE SNOWMAN.

43:49.895 --> 43:52.430
RENDERED FOUR STORIES HIGH,
MURPHY REQUIRES...

43:52.430 --> 43:55.400
[ Continues, Indistinct ]
HEY !

43:56.501 --> 43:59.237
ASSHOLE.
FATSO.

44:01.172 --> 44:03.241
HEY, SUSANNA.

44:03.241 --> 44:05.777
HEY.
JOHN--

44:05.777 --> 44:09.681
- CALL ME A CAB.
- OKAY, YOU'RE A CAB.

44:14.485 --> 44:17.555
[ Telephone Rings ]
LISA SAID YOU GOT
INTO DAISY'S ROOM.

44:17.555 --> 44:20.959
YES.
AND IT WAS FULL
OF CHICKENS !

44:20.959 --> 44:23.729
[ Nurse ]
SUSANNA, YOU HAVE
A PHONE CALL.

44:25.563 --> 44:27.365
HELLO ?

44:27.365 --> 44:29.968
[ Lisa ]
SO WHAT'S YOUR
"DIAG-NONSENSE" ?

44:29.968 --> 44:33.238
WHO IS THIS ?
WHAT'D HE SAY
TO MOM AND POP ?

44:42.113 --> 44:44.349
I HAVE A BORDERLINE PERSONALITY.

44:44.349 --> 44:47.118
[ Scoffs ]
WELL, THAT'S NOTHING.
WHAT ELSE ?

44:47.118 --> 44:50.688
HE DIDN'T WANT TO SAY.
HE THOUGHT IT WOULD
AFFECT MY RECOVERY.

44:50.688 --> 44:53.391
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.
TONGUE YOUR MEDS TONIGHT.

44:53.391 --> 44:56.394
AFTER 1:00 CHECKS,
GRETTA ALWAYS GOES OUT
FOR A SMOKE.

44:56.394 --> 45:00.265
CHECK THE MIRRORS,
AND IF THEY'RE CLEAR,
YOU GO DOWN TO HECTOR'S CLOSET.

45:00.265 --> 45:03.334
IT'S NEAR THE ART ROOM,
AND IT WILL BE OPEN.

45:19.818 --> 45:21.820
TORCH !

45:21.820 --> 45:25.156
COME ON.

45:35.366 --> 45:37.302
[ Laughter ]

45:41.506 --> 45:45.844
SUSANNA ! SUSANNA !
THIS IS HOW LISA GETS OUT
WHEN SHE ESCAPES.

45:49.647 --> 45:54.119
WE'RE UNDER
ADMINISTRATION, SO...
NO GOOD HERE.

45:54.119 --> 45:56.387
GOOD THING
THIS PLACE WORKS
ON A SLIDING SCALE.

45:56.387 --> 45:59.257
WE GET TO MINGLE
WITH THE LOCK-PICKING TRASH.

46:00.859 --> 46:03.528
[ Giggling ]
WHOO !

46:13.204 --> 46:15.006
WOW.

46:15.006 --> 46:17.775
HERE'S MISS DYKE !

46:18.910 --> 46:21.046
[ Giggling ]

46:22.747 --> 46:24.883
WHOO !

46:28.386 --> 46:30.455
SUSANNA, YOU'RE UP.

46:30.455 --> 46:33.458
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
I'VE ONLY DONE THIS
ONCE IN MY LIFE.

46:33.458 --> 46:36.828
COME ON !
COME ON !
WE CAME ALL THE WAY HERE.

46:36.828 --> 46:38.796
COME ON !

46:42.633 --> 46:45.670
* YOU KNOW THE NIGHTTIME *

46:45.670 --> 46:47.805
* IS THE RIGHT TIME *

46:49.607 --> 46:54.212
* OH, TO BE
BE WITH THE ONE YOU LOVE *

46:54.212 --> 46:56.814
- WHOO !
- ALL RIGHT !

46:56.814 --> 46:59.750
* COME ON, BABY *

46:59.750 --> 47:03.554
- * I WANT TO BE
WITH THE ONE I LOVE *
- YES !

47:03.554 --> 47:05.556
* AND YOU KNOW *

47:05.556 --> 47:09.427
- * JUST WHO I'M THINKIN' OF *
- WHOO !

47:10.929 --> 47:14.365
* TELL YOU
THE NIGHTTIME *

47:14.365 --> 47:16.567
* YEAH, IS THE RIGHT TIME *

47:16.567 --> 47:19.905
* OH, TO BE WITH THE ONE
YOU LOVE *

47:19.905 --> 47:23.975
- WHOO ! YEAH !
- [ Laughing ]

47:23.975 --> 47:26.177
** [ Continues ]

47:29.647 --> 47:31.849
WHEN THEY BUILT THIS PLACE,
THEY PUT THE TUNNELS IN...

47:31.849 --> 47:34.920
SO THE LOONIES
DIDN'T HAVE TO GO
ANYWHERE IN THE COLD.

47:34.920 --> 47:36.955
I MUST HAVE MISSED THAT
IN THE BROCHURE.

47:36.955 --> 47:40.926
* OH, COME ON, BABY
I NEED YOU *

47:40.926 --> 47:43.461
[ Janet ]
HEY, OPEN THE DOOR.

47:43.461 --> 47:47.198
* AND I WANT YOU
TO SQUEEZE ME *

47:47.198 --> 47:51.336
* YEAH, JUST AS TIGHT
AS YOU CAN *

47:51.336 --> 47:54.072
[ Fades ]
* I TELL YOU
THAT THE NIGHTTIME **

47:56.041 --> 47:58.910
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING ?

48:09.354 --> 48:13.291
[ Whispering ]
WOW. DR. WICK'S OFFICE.

48:27.772 --> 48:30.308
ALL RIGHT.
GEORGINA TUSKIN.

48:42.520 --> 48:44.455
SUSANNA KAYSEN.

48:46.924 --> 48:49.260
POLLY CLARK.

48:51.662 --> 48:54.065
CYNTHIA CROWLEY.

48:54.065 --> 48:56.267
CONGRATULATIONS.
THANK YOU.

48:57.535 --> 48:59.470
JANET WEBBER.

49:02.073 --> 49:04.209
LISA ROWE.

49:13.684 --> 49:15.620
[ Scoffs ]

49:37.708 --> 49:39.644
FUCK YOU, MELVIN.

49:44.115 --> 49:46.117
WANT TO SEE MINE ?

49:46.117 --> 49:48.286
LET ME SEE YOURS.

49:54.525 --> 49:56.461
[ Sighs ]

49:57.795 --> 50:00.998
[ Janet ]
"LISA ROWE.

50:00.998 --> 50:03.668
"HIGHS AND LOWS
INCREASINGLY SEVERE.

50:03.668 --> 50:07.172
"CONTROLLING RELATIONSHIPS
WITH PATIENTS.

50:07.172 --> 50:10.641
"NO APPRECIABLE RESPONSE
TO MEDS.

50:10.641 --> 50:12.910
NO REMISSION OBSERVED."

50:12.910 --> 50:15.280
THAT WAS BEFORE
YOU RAN AWAY.

50:15.280 --> 50:17.115
WE ARE VERY RARE,
AND WE ARE MOSTLY MEN.

50:17.115 --> 50:20.451
[ Janet ]
LISA THINKS SHE'S HOT SHIT
'CAUSE SHE'S A SOCIOPATH.

50:20.451 --> 50:22.920
I'M A SOCIOPATH.
NO, YOU'RE A DYKE.

50:22.920 --> 50:26.057
"BORDERLINE PERSONALITY
DISORDER.

50:26.057 --> 50:28.193
"AN INSTABILITY
OF SELF-IMAGE,

50:28.193 --> 50:29.994
"RELATIONSHIPS AND MOOD.

50:29.994 --> 50:33.464
"UNCERTAINTY ABOUT GOALS,
IMPULSIVE IN ACTIVITIES...

50:33.464 --> 50:38.103
"THAT ARE SELF-DAMAGING,
SUCH AS CASUAL SEX.

50:38.103 --> 50:40.238
I LIKE THAT.

50:40.238 --> 50:45.076
SOCIAL CONTRARINESS
AND A GENERALLY PESSIMISTIC
ATTITUDE ARE OFTEN OBSERVED."

50:46.511 --> 50:48.279
WELL, THAT'S ME.

50:48.279 --> 50:50.348
THAT'S EVERYBODY.

50:50.348 --> 50:53.184
I MEAN, WHAT KIND OF SEX
ISN'T CASUAL ?

50:53.184 --> 50:56.053
THEY MEAN PROMISCUOUS.

50:56.053 --> 50:58.389
I'M NOT PROMISCUOUS.

51:02.660 --> 51:04.229
I'M NOT.

51:21.646 --> 51:23.648
JESUS.

51:23.648 --> 51:25.583
LOOK AT JANET.

51:25.583 --> 51:27.585
[ Valerie ]
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

51:27.585 --> 51:30.488
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

51:30.488 --> 51:33.758
YOU KNOW, TAKING US
FOR ICE CREAMS
IN A BLIZZARD,

51:33.758 --> 51:36.627
MAKES YOU WONDER
WHO THE REAL
WHACK JOBS ARE.

51:36.627 --> 51:38.763
YOU KNOW, I THINK
IT'S KIND OF NICE.

51:38.763 --> 51:43.100
I MEAN, I THINK IT'S NICE
TO DO SOMETHING NICE
ON DAISY'S LAST DAY.

51:45.270 --> 51:47.405
** [ Easy-Listening
Christmas Carols ]

51:50.975 --> 51:53.378
[ Valerie ]
COME ON, COME ON.

51:53.378 --> 51:55.513
[ All Chattering ]

52:10.961 --> 52:14.799
- FUCK !
- I'M GONNA HAVE
PEPPERMINT STICK.

52:14.799 --> 52:18.203
- YEAH, ME TOO. CAN I JUST
HAVE PEPPERMINT STICK ?
- SURE.

52:18.203 --> 52:20.838
NO. IT'S JUST CALLED
PEPPERMINT.

52:20.838 --> 52:23.941
PEPPERMINT DICK !
[ Laughter ]
HONESTLY.

52:23.941 --> 52:25.876
PEPPERMINT CLIT !

52:25.876 --> 52:28.846
[ Laughter ]
[ Valerie ]
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

52:28.846 --> 52:33.318
- OKAY. WE'RE JUST GOING
TO HAVE FOUR CONES.
- FOUR CONES.

52:33.318 --> 52:35.453
SUSANNA, DO YOU WANT
ANYTHING ?

52:35.453 --> 52:37.822
I'M FINE.
LISA ?

52:42.193 --> 52:44.329
HEY, RONNY.

52:44.329 --> 52:46.331
YES ?
YOU GOT ANY HOT FUDGE ?

52:46.331 --> 52:48.333
YES.
YEAH ?

52:48.333 --> 52:52.203
CAN I HAVE A VANILLA SUNDAE
WITH HOT FUDGE...

52:52.203 --> 52:56.040
AND, UH, SPRINKLES--
RAINBOW, NOT CHOCOLATE.

52:56.040 --> 52:59.210
MM-HMM.
AND, UH,

52:59.210 --> 53:01.379
UM,

53:02.880 --> 53:06.617
WHIPPED CREAM, CHERRIES...

53:06.617 --> 53:08.519
AND, UH--

53:08.519 --> 53:11.422
- NUTS ?
- [ All Laughing ]

53:16.561 --> 53:20.331
OKAY, NOW. OKAY.
LET'S HAVE A SEAT,
LADIES.

53:23.301 --> 53:25.102
MELVIN...

53:25.102 --> 53:28.839
THOUGHT THAT I SHOULD
LIVE IN A HALFWAY HOUSE.
[ Scoffs ]

53:28.839 --> 53:32.710
BUT MY FATHER KNEW
THAT I DESERVED
MY OWN APARTMENT,

53:32.710 --> 53:35.179
SO HE GOT ME
THE PRETTIEST APARTMENT.

53:35.179 --> 53:37.248
IT HAS AN EAT-IN CHICKEN.

53:37.248 --> 53:41.752
AND ALL THIS BEAUTIFUL
WICKER FURNITURE,
WHICH IS FANTASTIC.

53:41.752 --> 53:43.554
WICKER BUTTERFLIES--

53:43.554 --> 53:47.692
MY VERY FAVORITE PART IS THAT
LIKE IN THE PHONE BOOTH...

53:47.692 --> 53:50.027
THERE'S A SIGN
RIGHT OUTSIDE...

53:50.027 --> 53:55.232
THAT SAYS,
"IF YOU LIVED HERE,
YOU'D BE HOME NOW."

53:55.232 --> 53:58.836
HELLO, SUSANNA.
DO YOU REMEMBER ME ?

53:58.836 --> 54:02.940
YOU MUST REMEMBER ME.
YES. MRS. GILCREST, HI.

54:02.940 --> 54:08.078
- SUSANNA, ARE YOU OKAY ?
- OH, I'M-- I'M FINE.

54:08.078 --> 54:11.248
HEY, BONNIE.
HOW'S RADCLIFFE ?
WELLESLEY.

54:11.248 --> 54:14.218
I'M ENJOYING IT.
IT'S STRONG IN ART.

54:14.218 --> 54:16.421
GOING TO THE SORBONNE
THIS SUMMER.
THAT'S GREAT.

54:16.421 --> 54:19.290
YOU KNOW,
I KNOW ALL ABOUT YOU.

54:19.290 --> 54:22.059
AND I HOPE
THEY PUT YOU AWAY FOREVER.

54:22.059 --> 54:26.096
- IS THIS
THE PROFESSOR'S WIFE ?
- WHAT PROFESSOR ?

54:26.096 --> 54:30.801
- OH, SO YOU TOLD EVERYBODY ?
- LADY, BACK OFF.

54:30.801 --> 54:32.803
WAS I TALKING TO YOU ?
MOTHER, WE HAVE TO GO.

54:32.803 --> 54:35.840
NO, YOU WERE SPITTING ON ME,
SO MELLOW FUCKIN' OUT.

54:35.840 --> 54:37.975
[ Mrs. Gilcrest ]
DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT TO DO.

54:37.975 --> 54:40.511
LOOK, SHE GAVE YOUR HUSBAND
A RIM JOB.
BIG FUCKIN' DEAL.

54:40.511 --> 54:43.948
I'M SURE HE WAS BEGGING FOR IT,
AND I HEARD IT WAS LIKE
A PENCIL ANYWAY.

54:43.948 --> 54:46.717
- WHY, YOU--
HOW DARE YOU !
- SOME ADVICE, OKAY ?

54:46.717 --> 54:49.654
JUST DON'T POINT
YOUR FUCKIN' FINGER
AT CRAZY PEOPLE !

54:49.654 --> 54:52.857
- [ Growling, Barking ]
- [ Howling ]

54:52.857 --> 54:55.526
LET GO OF ME !

54:55.526 --> 54:58.329
- MOTHER ?
- GET THAT OUT OF MY FACE,
ASSHOLE !

55:00.598 --> 55:05.135
- LET GO. NOW.
- [ Barking, Howling
Continue ]

55:05.135 --> 55:08.272
- STOP IT !
- [ Janet ]
RANK YOU !

55:08.272 --> 55:11.175
COME AGAIN,
MRS. PROFESSOR !

55:11.175 --> 55:13.778
[ Lisa ]
YOU SHARED A MAN
WITH THAT WOMAN ?

55:20.250 --> 55:22.252
DID YOU ENJOY
THE FRESH AIR, LISA ?

55:22.252 --> 55:24.054
YEAH, I DID, VAL.
THANKS.
GOOD.

55:24.054 --> 55:28.258
'CAUSE IT'S THE LAST TIME
YOU'RE LEAVING THE WARD.

55:28.258 --> 55:30.928
IS THAT A DARE,
OR A DOUBLE DARE ?

55:33.263 --> 55:35.566
[ Woman ]
OKAY, RAISE YOUR ARMS.
** [ Slow-Tempo Waltz ]

55:35.566 --> 55:38.102
VERY GOOD.
WE'RE GOING TO BE TREES.

55:38.102 --> 55:41.839
FEEL THE STRENGTH IN YOUR ARMS
AS THE BRANCHES,

55:41.839 --> 55:44.575
AND REACH THOSE BRANCHES
UP TO THE SKY--

55:44.575 --> 55:46.577
COME ON, SUSANNA.
REACH.

55:46.577 --> 55:48.579
VERY GOOD.
OH.

55:48.579 --> 55:50.981
LISA, GET ON.
ALL RIGHT.

55:50.981 --> 55:53.150
REACH YOUR ARMS, GIRLS.
REACH. REALLY LIFT.

55:53.150 --> 55:55.986
[ Meows ]
FEEL THE STRETCH
THROUGH THE HIP.

55:55.986 --> 55:58.389
[ Barks ]
VERY GOOD.
LET YOUR ARMS BE BRANCHES.

55:58.389 --> 56:01.125
[ Laughing ]
FEEL THE STRENGTH
OF THOSE BRANCHES.

56:01.125 --> 56:04.529
REACH.
REACH ALL THE WAY
UP INTO THE SKY.

56:04.529 --> 56:06.531
VERY GOOD.

56:06.531 --> 56:08.466
LET THE WINDS
BLOW THE LEAVES...

56:08.466 --> 56:12.069
[ Lisa Laughing ]
AND LET YOUR FINGERS
BE THE LEAVES.

56:12.069 --> 56:16.240
VERY GOOD.
FEEL THE WIND.
GOOD. GOOD, LISA.

56:16.240 --> 56:18.208
VERY GOOD.

56:18.208 --> 56:21.746
JUST LIFT UP. LIFT UP.
VERY GOOD, GIRLS.

56:21.746 --> 56:24.549
NOW, FEEL YOUR FEET.
FEEL YOUR FEET BE ROOTED.

56:24.549 --> 56:26.951
GO DOWN INTO A PLIE.
VERY GOOD.

56:26.951 --> 56:29.620
GOOD, GIRLS.
POLLY, VERY GOOD.

56:29.620 --> 56:33.758
OKAY. NOW STRETCH IT.
THE WIND'S BLOWING REALLY HARD.
THIS WAY. THIS WAY.

56:33.758 --> 56:35.826
IT'S BLOWING YOU OVER.
THAT'S NOT FAIR.

56:35.826 --> 56:37.828
[ Screaming ]
THAT'S NOT FAIR !

56:37.828 --> 56:39.964
[ Continues Screaming ]
THAT IS NOT FAIR !

56:39.964 --> 56:42.399
SEVENTY FOUR IS
THE PERFECT WEIGHT.

56:42.399 --> 56:45.202
[ Sobs ]

56:45.202 --> 56:47.404
GOOD LUCK,
CRAZY BITCH.

56:47.404 --> 56:50.975
[ Instructor ]
WHAT KIND OF TREE CAN YOU BE,
JANET, DOWN THERE ON THE
FLOOR ?

56:50.975 --> 56:53.711
[ Janet ]
I'M A FUCKING SHRUB,
ALL RIGHT ?

56:56.180 --> 56:58.483
** [ Minor-Key Ballad ]

56:59.850 --> 57:04.889
* HOW DO YOU FIGHT LONELINESS *

57:07.625 --> 57:11.762
* YOU SMILE ALL THE TIME *

57:15.165 --> 57:19.504
* SHOWIN' YOUR TEETH
TILL MEANINGLESS *

57:23.240 --> 57:28.045
* AND SHARPEN THEM WITH LIES *

57:30.515 --> 57:34.251
* AND WHATEVER IS GOING DOWN *

57:34.251 --> 57:36.053
...AND I CANNOT FIGHT BACK.

57:36.053 --> 57:38.455
YOU'RE USING ME.
I MEAN, IT'S SO CLEAR
THAT YOU'RE USING ME.

57:38.455 --> 57:42.326
* WILL FOLLOW YOU AROUND *
[ Susanna Continues,
Indistinct ]

57:42.326 --> 57:46.797
* THAT'S HOW YOU FIGHT
LONELINESS *
[ Shouting ]

57:50.400 --> 57:54.539
* YOU LAUGH AT EVERY JOKE *

57:59.276 --> 58:02.146
[ Laughing, Cheering ]

58:02.146 --> 58:06.483
* YOU DRAG
YOUR BLANKET BLINDLY *

58:09.887 --> 58:14.024
[ Chattering ]
* YOU FILL YOUR HEART
WITH SMOKE *

58:15.560 --> 58:17.762
[ Announcer ]
MARTIN LUTHER KING, JR.,
WAS KILLED TONIGHT...

58:17.762 --> 58:20.765
* AND THE FIRST THING
THAT YOU WANT *

58:20.765 --> 58:23.433
...AS HE STOOD ALONE
ON THE BALCONY
OF HIS HOTEL ROOM.

58:23.433 --> 58:28.839
LAST NIGHT, HE SAID THIS--
* WILL BE THE LAST THING
YOU EVER NEED *

58:28.839 --> 58:32.309
[ King ] WE'VE GOT
SOME DIFFICULT DAYS AHEAD.
* THAT'S HOW YOU FIGHT IT **

58:32.309 --> 58:35.913
BUT IT REALLY DOESN'T MATTER
WITH ME NOW.
** [ Fades ]

58:35.913 --> 58:39.917
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN
TO THE MOUNTAINTOP.
[ Applause ]

58:39.917 --> 58:42.119
I DON'T MIND.
I DON'T MIND.

58:43.954 --> 58:45.656
[ Man on TV ]
SO WHAT DO YOUR OTHER CHILDREN
CALL YOU ?

58:45.656 --> 58:49.594
WELL THEY'VE CALLED ME
MOM, AND MAMA, AND MOMMY...

58:49.594 --> 58:52.897
[ Door Shuts ]
[ Valerie ]
SUSANNA. YOU HAVE A VISITOR.

58:56.400 --> 58:58.803
WH-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE ?

59:01.305 --> 59:03.440
HI.

59:03.440 --> 59:06.143
I, UH, GOT TO SHIP OUT
NEXT WEEK.

59:06.143 --> 59:09.279
HERE.

59:15.586 --> 59:17.722
[ Both Chuckle ]

59:19.590 --> 59:21.726
[ Laughing ]

59:24.862 --> 59:28.465
[ Gretta ]
CHECKS.

59:28.465 --> 59:30.467
SORRY.

59:30.467 --> 59:32.269
NO. IT'S OKAY.

59:32.269 --> 59:34.705
WE HAVE TEN MINUTES
TILL THEY COME BACK.

59:34.705 --> 59:39.209
MEOW.
MEOW.

59:39.209 --> 59:41.145
[ Hisses ]

59:44.481 --> 59:46.483
HEY, TORCH.

59:46.483 --> 59:49.486
WHAT YOU DOING ?

59:49.486 --> 59:51.288
NOTHING.

59:51.288 --> 59:56.493
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU GO
TO YOUR ROOM AND DO NOTHING,
HUH ?

59:56.493 --> 59:59.897
[ Sobbing ]

01:00:06.236 --> 01:00:09.339
[ Margie ]
CHECKS.

01:00:09.339 --> 01:00:12.276
CHECKS.

01:00:14.244 --> 01:00:16.180
CHECKS.

01:00:19.249 --> 01:00:21.385
HEY, MARGIE.
HEY, LISA.

01:00:21.385 --> 01:00:23.387
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?
CHECKS.

01:00:23.387 --> 01:00:25.389
HOW'S JOE ?

01:00:25.389 --> 01:00:27.024
HE'S FINE.
YEAH.

01:00:27.024 --> 01:00:28.959
LISA, I HAVE TO DO MY CHECKS.

01:00:28.959 --> 01:00:32.529
YEAH, AND WHAT ?
TAKING FIVE MINUTES FOR ME
WOULD BE A DERELICTION OF DUTY ?

01:00:32.529 --> 01:00:35.666
WHAT IF I HAD
A PUNCTURED ARTERY ?
WHAT WOULD YOU DO ?

01:00:35.666 --> 01:00:38.268
WOULD YOU JUST KEEP
GOING ABOUT YOUR ROUNDS
AND IGNORE MY WOUNDS ?

01:00:38.268 --> 01:00:41.205
- LISA, STOP IT.
- STOP WHAT ? YOU FUCKING--
LOOK AT THIS.

01:00:41.205 --> 01:00:44.141
- GO AHEAD. GO AHEAD.
- THAT'S ENOUGH.

01:00:44.141 --> 01:00:47.144
TAKE ONE FUCKING STEP
AND I'LL JAM THIS IN MY AORTA.
GO AHEAD.

01:00:47.144 --> 01:00:50.815
STOP IT.
LISA, YOUR AORTA IS
IN YOUR CHEST.

01:00:52.249 --> 01:00:54.084
GOOD TO KNOW.

01:00:54.084 --> 01:00:56.520
I'LL MAKE
A NOTE OF THAT.

01:00:56.520 --> 01:00:59.523
GOOD.

01:00:59.523 --> 01:01:01.591
MEOW.

01:01:01.591 --> 01:01:03.728
[ Laughs, Whistles ]

01:01:05.395 --> 01:01:09.333
SUSANNA, YOU HAVE
GROUNDS PRIVILEGES.
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A WALK ?

01:01:09.333 --> 01:01:12.236
GO GET A CUP OF COFFEE.
[ Cheering, Laughing ]

01:01:12.236 --> 01:01:14.171
[ Panting, Moaning ]

01:01:15.339 --> 01:01:18.308
[ Sighs ]
WE SHOULD
GET OUT OF HERE.

01:01:33.791 --> 01:01:35.592
THE CAF--
THE CAFETERIA IS THIS WAY.

01:01:35.592 --> 01:01:37.795
JUST KEEP WALKING.
MY WHEELS ARE RIGHT HERE.
WAIT.

01:01:37.795 --> 01:01:40.030
WH-WHAT ARE WE DOING ?

01:01:42.566 --> 01:01:44.802
[ Whispering ]
WE'RE GOING TO CANADA.

01:01:47.237 --> 01:01:50.440
SUSANNA.

01:01:50.440 --> 01:01:53.077
YOU'RE NOT CRAZY.
OKAY ?

01:01:53.077 --> 01:01:55.212
YOU DON'T NEED
TO BE HERE.

01:01:56.246 --> 01:01:58.849
I TRIED TO KILL MYSELF,
TOBY.

01:01:58.849 --> 01:02:01.651
BUT--
Y-YOU TOOK SOME ASPIRIN--

01:02:01.651 --> 01:02:03.921
I TOOK A BOTTLE OF ASPIRIN.

01:02:03.921 --> 01:02:06.791
WHA--
AND THAT BUYS YOU
A YEAR IN THIS PLACE ?

01:02:06.791 --> 01:02:08.926
THAT-- SUSANNA,
TH-THAT'S BULLSHIT, OKAY ?

01:02:08.926 --> 01:02:10.727
THEY'RE BREAKING YOU.

01:02:10.727 --> 01:02:14.331
NOW, COME ON. ALL RIGHT ?
E-EVERYTHING IS CHANGING, MAN.

01:02:14.331 --> 01:02:17.067
WH-WHAT THE FUCK
DO THEY KNOW
ABOUT BEING NORMAL ?

01:02:18.068 --> 01:02:21.738
I-- I HAVE FRIENDS IN HERE.

01:02:22.672 --> 01:02:25.542
WHO ?
THEM ?

01:02:25.542 --> 01:02:27.912
THOSE GIRLS ?
SUSANNA.

01:02:27.912 --> 01:02:31.816
THEY'RE EATING GRAPES
OFF OF THE WALLPAPER.

01:02:31.816 --> 01:02:35.419
OKAY ?
TH-THEY'RE INSANE.

01:02:35.419 --> 01:02:38.355
IF THEY ARE, I AM.

01:02:39.689 --> 01:02:42.226
NO. NO, BABY.

01:02:42.226 --> 01:02:44.361
LISTEN,
COME WITH ME.
NO.

01:02:48.833 --> 01:02:51.101
LOOK, MY, UH--

01:02:51.101 --> 01:02:54.771
MY DAD GAVE ME
FIVE GRAND. OKAY ?

01:02:54.771 --> 01:02:58.575
WE CAN GO UP THERE.
WE COULD BUILD A CABIN
IN THE WOODS.

01:02:58.575 --> 01:03:00.577
SUSANNA.

01:03:00.577 --> 01:03:03.013
LOOK, I KNOW
IT SOUNDS CRAZY...

01:03:04.748 --> 01:03:07.151
BUT I THINK I LOVE YOU.

01:03:07.151 --> 01:03:10.287
SO COME WITH ME, OKAY ?

01:03:12.356 --> 01:03:14.291
COME WITH ME.

01:03:20.364 --> 01:03:22.366
UH.

01:03:22.366 --> 01:03:24.434
YOU WANT TO LEAVE.

01:03:24.434 --> 01:03:27.337
DON'T YOU ?
I MEAN, IT-IT--
YES.

01:03:27.337 --> 01:03:29.573
I WANT TO LEAVE.

01:03:32.910 --> 01:03:35.312
BUT NOT WITH YOU.

01:03:38.648 --> 01:03:40.817
NOT WITH YOU.

01:03:41.785 --> 01:03:43.921
I'M SORRY.

01:03:44.955 --> 01:03:47.091
SUSANNA, WAIT A SECOND.

01:04:33.037 --> 01:04:35.172
WHY DID YOU DO THAT ?

01:04:38.775 --> 01:04:41.345
FIX THE LIGHTBULB
AT NIGHT ?

01:04:43.313 --> 01:04:46.183
I'M NOT HERE IN THE MORNING,

01:04:46.183 --> 01:04:49.253
AND THAT'S WHEN YOU LIKE
TO DRAW YOUR PICTURES AND STUFF.

01:04:49.253 --> 01:04:51.288
SO--

01:04:52.389 --> 01:04:54.291
UH-HUH.

01:05:00.965 --> 01:05:03.233
JOHN.

01:05:04.601 --> 01:05:06.636
YEAH.

01:05:10.574 --> 01:05:12.509
WHY DO YOU LIKE ME ?

01:05:15.579 --> 01:05:18.715
I JUST LIKE YOU.

01:05:18.715 --> 01:05:20.417
THAT'S ALL.

01:05:21.651 --> 01:05:24.421
I WISH YOU WERE GETTING
BETTER, THOUGH.

01:05:24.421 --> 01:05:26.790
I WOULD, UH--

01:05:26.790 --> 01:05:31.528
[ Chuckles ]
I WOULD TAKE YOU OUT
TO GO SEE A MOVIE OR SOMETHING.

01:05:34.131 --> 01:05:37.101
THAT WOULD BE NICE.

01:05:37.101 --> 01:05:39.669
[ Woman Shouting,
Objects Clattering ]

01:05:42.139 --> 01:05:45.275
MY FACE. I'M OKAY.

01:05:45.275 --> 01:05:48.078
JUST-JUST STEP--
LET HER BE.
SHE'S FINE. SHE'S FINE.

01:05:48.078 --> 01:05:52.249
[ Wailing ]
[ Nurse ] SECLUSION.
TAKE HER TO SECLUSION. COME ON.

01:05:52.249 --> 01:05:54.884
[ Sobbing ]
I GOT YOU.

01:05:54.884 --> 01:05:58.788
MY FACE.
MY FACE. WHY ?

01:05:58.788 --> 01:06:03.293
MY FACE !
MY FACE !

01:06:03.293 --> 01:06:05.962
QUIETEN DOWN.
QUIETEN DOWN.

01:06:05.962 --> 01:06:07.998
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

01:06:07.998 --> 01:06:11.235
[ Fading ]
MY FACE ! I'M UGLY !

01:06:16.073 --> 01:06:18.208
[ Polly Weeping ]

01:06:23.480 --> 01:06:25.515
[ Man On TV ]
THE SKETCHES AND PLANS
YOU WILL SEE TODAY...

01:06:25.515 --> 01:06:29.886
WILL SHOW CLEARLY
THE ENORMOUS SIZE
AND SCOPE OF OUR PROJECT.

01:06:29.886 --> 01:06:34.358
AND THE IMPORTANT THING
IS THAT DISNEY WORLD
IS LOCATED...

01:06:34.358 --> 01:06:36.660
JUST A FEW MILES
FROM THE CROSSING POINT--

01:06:36.660 --> 01:06:39.329
[ Susanna ]
HEY.
[ TV continues ]

01:06:39.329 --> 01:06:41.698
WHAT HAPPENED TO POLLY ?

01:06:43.800 --> 01:06:47.237
WHAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN ?
NO ONE IS EVER GOING
TO KISS HER, MAN.

01:06:49.406 --> 01:06:52.542
THEY'RE BUILDING
A NEW DISNEYLAND
IN FLORIDA.

01:06:52.542 --> 01:06:57.013
IF I COULD HAVE ANY JOB
IN THE WORLD, I'D BE
A PROFESSIONAL CINDERELLA.

01:06:57.013 --> 01:06:59.015
YOU COULD BE SNOW WHITE.

01:06:59.015 --> 01:07:00.817
AND POLLY COULD BE
MINNIE MOUSE.

01:07:00.817 --> 01:07:03.487
AND THEN EVERYONE WOULD
HUG HER AND KISS HER
AND LOVE HER...

01:07:03.487 --> 01:07:06.090
AND NO ONE WOULD KNOW
WHAT WAS INSIDE
THAT BIG GIANT HEAD,

01:07:06.090 --> 01:07:08.825
YOU KNOW ?

01:07:08.825 --> 01:07:11.095
GIVE ME YOUR KEYS.

01:07:29.379 --> 01:07:32.116
[ Weeping Continues ]

01:07:36.853 --> 01:07:38.788
HEY, POLLY.

01:07:40.124 --> 01:07:43.127
IT'S SUSANNA.
JUST PLAY SOMETHING.

01:07:43.127 --> 01:07:46.130
IF TALKING DID SHIT,
WE'D BE OUT OF HERE BY NOW.

01:07:46.130 --> 01:07:48.265
COME ON.

01:07:58.608 --> 01:08:00.544
* THE *

01:08:03.347 --> 01:08:06.183
UH--

01:08:07.784 --> 01:08:09.586
* WHEN YOU'RE ALONE *

01:08:09.586 --> 01:08:11.921
* AND LIFE IS MAKING
YOU LONELY *

01:08:11.921 --> 01:08:15.325
* YOU CAN ALWAYS GO *

01:08:15.325 --> 01:08:17.827
[ Laughing ]
* DOWNTOWN *

01:08:19.763 --> 01:08:21.698
[ Silence ]

01:08:25.202 --> 01:08:27.203
* WHEN YOU'VE GOT WORRIES *

01:08:27.203 --> 01:08:29.939
* ALL THE NOISE AND THE HURRY *

01:08:29.939 --> 01:08:32.709
* SEEMS TO HELP I KNOW *

01:08:34.778 --> 01:08:36.746
[ Tambourine Jangling ]

01:08:40.350 --> 01:08:43.987
* DOWNTOWN *

01:08:43.987 --> 01:08:49.158
* JUST LISTEN TO THE MUSIC
IN THE TRAFFIC IN THE CITY *

01:08:49.158 --> 01:08:54.198
* LINGER ON THE SIDEWALKS
WHERE THE NEON LIGHTS
ARE PRETTY *

01:08:54.198 --> 01:08:58.768
* HOW CAN YOU LOSE *

01:08:58.768 --> 01:09:01.738
* THE LIGHTS ARE
MUCH BRIGHTER THERE *

01:09:01.738 --> 01:09:04.573
* YOU CAN FORGET ALL YOUR
TROUBLES *

01:09:04.573 --> 01:09:06.743
* FORGET ALL YOUR CARES
AND GO *

01:09:06.743 --> 01:09:08.845
BACK TO YOUR ROOM,
PLEASE.
* DOWNTOWN *

01:09:08.845 --> 01:09:11.180
PLEASE, BACK IN YOUR ROOM.
* THINGS WILL BE GREAT
WHEN YOU'RE *

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:13.250
* DOWNTOWN *

01:09:13.250 --> 01:09:15.319
McWILLEY IS GOING TO WAKE UP.
* EVERYTHING'S WAITING FOR YOU*

01:09:15.319 --> 01:09:18.322
SUSANNA, GIVE ME
THE GUITAR.
* JUST LISTEN TO THE RHYTHM *

01:09:18.322 --> 01:09:20.823
SO YOU'RE GOING
TO GET ME FIRED. LISA--

01:09:20.823 --> 01:09:24.594
* YOU'LL BE DANCING WITH HIM TO
BEFORE THE NIGHT IS OVER *

01:09:24.594 --> 01:09:26.962
SUSANNA,
GIVE ME THE GUITAR.
* HAPPY AGAIN *

01:09:26.962 --> 01:09:30.133
- * AGAIN *
- NO. NO.

01:09:30.133 --> 01:09:31.935
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY. COME HERE.

01:09:31.935 --> 01:09:34.703
YOU'RE GOING TO GET ME FIRED.
DO YOU KNOW THAT ? YOU--

01:09:46.182 --> 01:09:50.319
[ Polly ]
* DOWNTOWN *

01:09:50.319 --> 01:09:53.055
* EVERYTHING'S GREAT *

01:09:53.055 --> 01:09:57.627
* WHEN YOU'RE DOWNTOWN **

01:10:03.467 --> 01:10:06.503
[ Door Opens ]

01:10:23.487 --> 01:10:25.489
I'M WRITING YOU UP.

01:10:25.489 --> 01:10:28.224
I AM SICK OF THIS BULLSHIT.

01:10:32.962 --> 01:10:35.365
[ Woman ]
IS SHE HERE ?

01:10:35.365 --> 01:10:37.567
YOU CAN GO IN NOW.

01:10:42.872 --> 01:10:44.908
[ Woman Whispering ]
WHAT DID SHE DO ?

01:10:44.908 --> 01:10:47.477
[ Woman 2 ]
THEY DRUGGED
NURSE McWILLEY.

01:10:53.383 --> 01:10:55.385
GOOD MORNING, SUSANNA.
GOOD MORNING.

01:10:55.385 --> 01:10:57.521
HOW ARE YOU ?

01:10:58.988 --> 01:11:01.891
I'M FINE, I GUESS.

01:11:01.891 --> 01:11:04.828
SIT DOWN.

01:11:13.770 --> 01:11:15.739
YOU LOOK TIRED.

01:11:17.574 --> 01:11:19.576
POLLY FREAKED OUT LAST NIGHT...

01:11:19.576 --> 01:11:22.879
AND WE STAYED UP
SINGING TO HER, LISA AND I.

01:11:24.448 --> 01:11:26.850
HAVE YOU BECOME FRIENDS
WITH LISA ?

01:11:29.319 --> 01:11:31.321
WHY ?
IS THAT BAD ?

01:11:31.321 --> 01:11:33.957
DOES IT FEEL BAD ?
NO.

01:11:33.957 --> 01:11:38.061
BEFORE YOU CAME HERE
DID YOU HAVE
MANY GIRLFRIENDS ?

01:11:38.061 --> 01:11:39.629
NOT REALLY.

01:11:41.465 --> 01:11:45.935
WOULD YOU SAY THAT
BEFORE YOU CAME HERE
YOUR FRIENDS CONSISTED MAINLY...

01:11:45.935 --> 01:11:47.537
OF BOYS, OF MEN ?

01:11:48.872 --> 01:11:51.741
DOES IT SAY IN THERE
THAT I'M PROMISCUOUS ?

01:11:51.741 --> 01:11:54.143
WHY DO YOU CHOOSE THAT WORD ?

01:11:54.143 --> 01:11:56.145
HOW MANY GUYS
WOULD I HAVE TO SLEEP WITH...

01:11:56.145 --> 01:12:00.950
TO BE CONSIDERED PROMISCUOUS--
TEXTBOOK PROMISCUOUS ?

01:12:00.950 --> 01:12:03.019
WHAT DO YOU THINK ?

01:12:03.019 --> 01:12:06.756
TEN, EIGHT, FIVE.

01:12:06.756 --> 01:12:10.894
AND HOW MANY GIRLS WOULD A GUY
MY AGE HAVE TO SLEEP WITH
TO BE CONSIDERED PROMISCUOUS ?

01:12:10.894 --> 01:12:12.962
TEN, 20, 109 ?

01:12:12.962 --> 01:12:14.998
WELL, SOMEONE
WHO'S COMPULSIVELY
PROMISCUOUS...

01:12:14.998 --> 01:12:18.702
MIGHT ENGAGE IN A SEX ACT
WITH A GUEST IN THEIR ROOM,

01:12:18.702 --> 01:12:20.904
AND THEN ENGAGE
IN ANOTHER SEX ACT--

01:12:20.904 --> 01:12:22.906
DURING THE SAME DAY--

01:12:22.906 --> 01:12:24.941
WITH AN ORDERLY.

01:12:27.977 --> 01:12:30.447
AM I IN TROUBLE
FOR KISSING AN ORDERLY,

01:12:30.447 --> 01:12:32.949
OR GIVING MY BOYFRIEND
A BLOW JOB ?

01:12:35.051 --> 01:12:37.120
MELVIN SAYS...

01:12:37.120 --> 01:12:41.458
YOU HAVE SOME VERY INTERESTING
THEORIES ABOUT YOUR ILLNESS.

01:12:41.458 --> 01:12:46.463
YOU BELIEVE THERE IS
A MYSTICAL UNDERTOW IN LIFE--

01:12:46.463 --> 01:12:49.132
QUICKSANDS OF SHADOWS.

01:12:49.132 --> 01:12:51.334
YEAH, AND ANOTHER
ONE OF MY THEORIES IS THAT...

01:12:51.334 --> 01:12:53.870
YOU PEOPLE DON'T KNOW
